


translate English day5_my_T_976ba497:


    br "\n What I first mistook for something entirely insignificant--a misunderstanding of sort--sprouted a tiny bud of doubt that quickly blossomed into alarming suspicion.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_my_T_11b1e7a2:


    extend "\nI'm talking about her, of course. This goes far beyond simple paranoia or even a hilarious anecdote.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_my_T_603e44eb:


    extend "\nIf my assumptions are correct, then I need to find out more about her.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_my_T_2153efa3:


    extend "\nAngels, by their very nature, are born to follow the word of God, and while they do co-exist with humans, they cannot stay by their sides for long.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_my_T_7fb14558:


    extend "\nThey exist on this unfamiliar and frightening mortal plain, harboring secrets that even they don't fully comprehend.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_my_T_4a8b6325:


    extend "\nI can't let her go without first making sure my soul is prepared."


translate English day5_my_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_my_T_0f914019:


    nar "I had left the infirmary and was heading toward the exit when I come to a halt in the middle of the hallway."


translate English day5_my_T_62b49159:


    nar "It's Maya. She's all alone and oddly distressed, occasionally lifting her head to gaze down the hall leading to the infirmary."


translate English day5_my_T_367ccde8:


    nar "Is she waiting for someone?"


translate English day5_my_T_72cd9e40:


    pl "Maya!"


translate English day5_my_T_40c6c811:


    my "[na2]?"


translate English day5_my_T_7fc22691:


    nar "Her shoulders begin trembling faintly in response to the sound of her name."


translate English day5_my_T_a4f5179d:


    nar "She turns, an expression of surprise on her face that quickly softens when she realizes it's me."


translate English day5_my_T_4a61fb67:


    my "Should you be up and about already? I really think you should rest..."


translate English day5_my_T_2e6bce1c:


    pl "I'm fine, promise. Besides, being trapped inside is boring. {w}What are you doing here? Where's everyone else?"


translate English day5_my_T_2cfd410f:


    my "Um... Well, you see..."


translate English day5_my_T_a1f36ad1:


    my "I was really worried about you, [na2], so I decided to stay behind..."


translate English day5_my_T_ed736692:


    pl "You were waiting for me?! I hope you weren't here for too long... but also, I'm really glad you did! Thanks, Maya!"


translate English day5_my_T_6d5d3546:


    my "I'm not in pain and feeling great! It's all thanks to how sweet you were, coming to see me."


translate English day5_my_T_1601c9bc:


    pl "I'm not in pain and I'm feeling great! It's all thanks to how sweet you were, coming to see me."


translate English day5_my_T_9c89d078:


    pl "I was on my way back, so do you want to join me?"


translate English day5_my_T_d9ea6469:


    my "Mm-hm. Is there somewhere you need to be?"


translate English day5_my_T_78c4a2b0:


    pl "Yep. Is there somewhere you need to be?"


translate English day5_my_T_1928be33:


    my "N-No, nowhere in particular. I guess I'll come, too."


translate English day5_my_T_bf62a601:


    nar "The gloomy temple corridor seem to merge with the overcast sky."


translate English day5_my_T_28d0e20b:


    nar "As I walk beside Maya down the unpleasantly silent hallway, I feel like I've finally slipped back into my normal routine."


translate English day5_my_T_a51b191c:


    nar "Like I've gone back to those days in the beginning where I had nothing to worry about except focusing on my own business and following orders."


translate English day5_my_T_3cfcc123:


    pl "I'm really sorry about everything that happened today, Maya. It's thanks to me that you got tangled up in all this..."


translate English day5_my_T_c8eafd00:


    my "It's fine... None of it is your fault, [na2]. Besides, it's my fault that you ended up getting hurt..."


translate English day5_my_T_4d3ec468:


    pl "That had absolutely nothing to do with you! To be honest... *sigh*... this could go on forever."


translate English day5_my_T_691e14dd:


    pl "There's no point in talking about this anymore. All that matters is that you're okay."


translate English day5_my_T_e00586a7:


    my "Thank you, [na2]... for everything."


translate English day5_my_T_ab59cb16:


    nar "She says \"thank you\" almost as much as she says \"I'm sorry.\""


translate English day5_my_T_5c86bed8:


    nar "I'm just glad that she listened to me and took me seriously."


translate English day5_my_T_a0d97156:


    pl "He really scared the shit out of me, though! You know who I mean..."


translate English day5_my_T_2fc7a98d:


    pl "Speaking of which, were you able to have a serious conversation with Securett?"


translate English day5_my_T_7aed653d:


    my "Yes. He apologized and we talked about a couple other things as well."


translate English day5_my_T_5184948a:


    my "I didn't think I'd be back on talking terms with Cue again, so I'm overjoyed we were able to clear things up."


translate English day5_my_T_99e4d376:


    my "Also, the things that were said this morning weren't entirely wrong..."


translate English day5_my_T_0954dd2c:


    pl "You mean that stuff about your sister?"


translate English day5_my_T_f2108997:


    my "No... {w}Though I wonder if she ended up heading home after all..."


translate English day5_my_T_8181d809:


    pl "Which sounds exactly like what I heard this morning..."


translate English day5_my_T_5fcd82d0:


    nar "I quickly snap my mouth shut, cutting off the words involuntarily gushing from my mouth. It's not my place to say anything."


translate English day5_my_T_7206adf5:


    pl "S-Sorry, Maya. I'm just worried about you."


translate English day5_my_T_3d237095:


    my "It's okay... You don't have to apologize. Actually... It makes me feel a lot better hearing you say that."


translate English day5_my_T_ad7a7d1a:


    pl "Good then."


translate English day5_my_T_30e0b8ac:


    my "Ah...are you curious? About my family, that is..."


translate English day5_my_T_e58e290f:


    pl "Hm? Please don't feel like you have to dig up painful memories best left buried."


translate English day5_my_T_b8312aa5:


    pl "Of course, I'm happy to listen if you want to talk about it. {w}I still don't know much about you, Maya..."


translate English day5_my_T_7480d2bb:


    my "Okay..."


translate English day5_my_T_8d88e9cf:


    my "As I'm sure you know, I come from a small family who live outside the capital."


translate English day5_my_T_b4bdab80:


    my "I say \"family\" but none of us are related by blood. I guess it would be more accurate to call it a boarding school of sorts..."


translate English day5_my_T_71223e57:


    my "The Elvetts, a husband and wife, took ten of us in and raised us as their own."


translate English day5_my_T_ec005b59:


    my "They send us off to the temple once we come of age. {w}Which is why there are so many priests working here with the last name of Elvett."


translate English day5_my_T_ae6f582c:


    pl "I see... {w}I understand now why that girl called you her step-sister on our first day here. It's similar to my own hometown."


translate English day5_my_T_811468ac:


    pl "Though it sounds like your situation is actually pretty different. The complete opposite, in fact."


translate English day5_my_T_7e68ae8b:


    my "Opposite how?"


translate English day5_my_T_abe813a0:


    pl "I wouldn't know how it feels as someone who grew up in the capital, but... {w}my entire village is one giant family."


translate English day5_my_T_70ade8d5:


    pl "Everyone in the village is related in someway, whether as distant relatives or close blood ties. {w}Specific parentage gets complicated and hazy."


translate English day5_my_T_897f5c17:


    pl "But no one cares about that. {w}It's such a jumbled mess that folks end up raising someone else's kids without knowing who they actually belong to."


translate English day5_my_T_44fc1ea9:


    pl "And because of that, we grow up viewing everyone around us as our siblings."


translate English day5_my_T_d4f8201a:


    my "That's a lot of siblings..."


translate English day5_my_T_7fed3afe:


    pl "I'm not saying I hated it or that I thought the situation was problematic... {w}Actually, I'm pretty embarrassed telling you all this."


translate English day5_my_T_1e09ca75:


    nar "Maya so rarely initiates conversation, especially one this personal. Honestly, I was hoping by offering up a rare glimpse into my life, she might open up in response."


translate English day5_my_T_d627526b:


    nar "But my good intentions seem to have failed, as she remains tight lipped, unsure what to say in response."


translate English day5_my_T_c58290b5:


    nar "At the rate things are going, I'm afraid the conversation will end before it really began."


translate English day5_my_T_fe8fe5ed:


    my "If you didn't hate it that much, then why did you leave?"


translate English day5_my_T_d741775f:


    nar "The last question I thought she would ask suddenly pops from her mouth."


translate English day5_my_T_d253f998:


    nar "My brain starts working overtime as I try to formulate an answer before realizing that's completely unnecessary."


translate English day5_my_T_a30498db:


    pl "Just because I didn't hate the way I was raised doesn't mean I liked it, either."


translate English day5_my_T_79a254f7:


    nar "My village didn't feel like home to me. There was more I wanted to do in life, and I couldn't do any of it there."


translate English day5_my_T_3bcb00d5:


    nar "That's all. {w}It's how I truly felt at the time, though it's been a while since I thought back that far."


translate English day5_my_T_e1c33983:


    my "Which is why you moved to the capital?"


translate English day5_my_T_6fb9f241:


    pl "Yeah... Pretty ridiculous, huh?"


translate English day5_my_T_e69de60b:


    my "No... I think it's pretty amazing."


translate English day5_my_T_f838a71f:


    pl "I w-wouldn't go that far!!!"


translate English day5_my_T_252b3b25:


    my "I'm serious... I think people who have dreams and goals are amazing. {w}I don't have either of those things..."


translate English day5_my_T_45f8e541:


    pl "I'm far from the type of guy who lives my life working toward some special dream or lofty goal!"


translate English day5_my_T_565350d9:


    pl "I just do what I want... {w}And isn't that how you live your life, Maya? It makes things easier."


translate English day5_my_T_425fd707:


    my "I have vague ideas of what I'd like to do... {w}but since I can't accomplish any of them by myself, I tend to give up before I've started."


translate English day5_my_T_9e7bddb4:


    my "Everything else is too insignificant to bring me any joy in accomplishing them..."


translate English day5_my_T_1a55e713:


    pl "Like what? I want to know now! Maybe there's something I can help you with?"


translate English day5_my_T_57207fa6:


    my "N-None of it is interesting enough to share..."


translate English day5_my_T_8d9b57f3:


    my "And besides, this was all a very long time ago. {w}There's nothing I really want to do now..."


translate English day5_my_T_d12c5779:


    my "I used to have so many things that I liked and so many things that I wanted to do... {w}But I don't feel that way about anything anymore..."


translate English day5_my_T_4b90ce2c:


    pl "You still love flowers and animals, right?"


translate English day5_my_T_b1805cd4:


    my "Yes, but there's a limit as to what flowers and animals can exist within the temple grounds, and lately, the only cats or birds I see are dead..."


translate English day5_my_T_9c6ee49a:


    my "It makes me incredibly sad when I come across them."


translate English day5_my_T_4e0ea55c:


    pl "The work we do is pretty exhausting."


translate English day5_my_T_ea791f04:


    my "It's true. I feel the same way."


translate English day5_my_T_321530c2:


    pl "Maya... Do you plan on doing this forever?"


translate English day5_my_T_a1bdb7e6:


    nar "A brief jolt of anxiety passes through my mind as her depressing narrative continues."


translate English day5_my_T_8b11c0a8:


    nar "She lowers her head without answering. {w}Seeing her like that, I force myself to suppress my growing irritation."


translate English day5_my_T_1fdb1f45:


    pl "But hey, we've been here for five days already, right? I've already gotten used to what our job here entails."


translate English day5_my_T_102199a0:


    my "I believe you were the one who said it's ONLY been five days, right? {w}Everyone around us is quickly getting the hang of things, while I'm still struggling to make sense of it all."


translate English day5_my_T_e5772e44:


    my "I'm only slowing you and everyone else around us down, leading to incidents like what happened earlier today..."


translate English day5_my_T_9ecafcd9:


    pl "I already told you, don't worry about today! Like you said, it's only been five days, right? {w}I'm sure you'll quickly get the hang of things moving forward."


translate English day5_my_T_956914fb:


    my "You really think so?"


translate English day5_my_T_93106113:


    pl "Huh?"


translate English day5_my_T_a7edeba4:


    my "You work beside me every day, so you would know better than anyone. Do you really think I'm going to get better at this?"


translate English day5_my_T_ddf0773b:


    nar "I find myself at a loss for words. {w}But I'd be lying if I said I've never doubted her capability regarding her job performance."


translate English day5_my_T_4730bbc0:


    pl "I know so. {w}You're absolutely going to excel."


translate English day5_my_T_17c79e5c:


    nar "I hastily force out the words that were tangled in my throat, but my pause before hand, no matter how brief, took on an unfortunate significance in her mind."


translate English day5_my_T_1f4543f9:


    nar "I swallow another mouthful of spit down my dry throat. {w}Up until now, anytime I counseled someone else or listened to their complaints,"


translate English day5_my_T_42e70c68:


    nar "I always felt that telling someone to \"just forget about it,\" was the best advise there was. However, now that I find myself in the potential position of the advisee,"


translate English day5_my_T_db55ab28:


    nar "I realize I can't bring myself to say the words I could so easily utter before. {w}That she might follow that advice fills me with dread."


translate English day5_my_T_7fa8ecfc:


    pl "Your fastidiousness coupled with your, at times, childish personality, makes you come off as slow to the people around us."


translate English day5_my_T_6c1e9cda:


    pl "You may only see that as a disadvantage now, but I promise that it will most certainly help you in the future."


translate English day5_my_T_5039d1fa:


    pl "I believe in you, Maya, just like I've been saying this whole time... {w}Is the real problem that you don't believe in yourself?"


translate English day5_my_T_98f97020:


    my "No, I really want to be able to do my job right..."


translate English day5_my_T_2717d9a6:


    pl "Then do it. {w}There are far too many folks rotting away in our society who don't feel like they can do anything."


translate English day5_my_T_3ab744bc:


    pl "That you know you can do it in your heart is great! {w}And of course, if there's anything I can do to help you, I will."


translate English day5_my_T_ef53701a:


    pl "You should never feel afraid to ask for help when you need it, Maya. {w}Also..."


translate English day5_my_T_dc0b12b4:


    pl "You mentioned that you and Securett are back on good terms? {w}I know that he'll be more than happy to help you as well."


translate English day5_my_T_20cb502b:


    nar "I have no idea what I'm saying anymore. {w}The words just seem to come pouring forth, one after the other."


translate English day5_my_T_ddb22a52:


    nar "I'm just praying that, from within my flood of words, something sticks in her mind."


translate English day5_my_T_55e68bb0:


    my "You really think so?"


translate English day5_my_T_100deaa3:


    pl "Really really! I'm always serious when it's about you, Maya."


translate English day5_my_T_d0260ed7:


    my "Why?"


translate English day5_my_T_0e80542e:


    nar "Her face is scrunched up with anxiety."


translate English day5_my_T_57a4b79c:


    my "You're always so nice to me, [na2], and it scares me... {w}B-because there's nothing I can give you in return..."


translate English day5_my_T_bed1ab73:


    pl "Just getting to spend time with you like this is all I need."


translate English day5_my_T_98d743a2:


    nar "It's true. {w}I repeat my words of sincerity for the umpteenth time. It's starting to sound more and more like a vow of sorts."


translate English day5_my_T_9e14c0fc:


    nar "Or maybe more like a magic spell. {w}A spell designed to temporarily cast away insecurity and doubt."


translate English day5_my_T_314d0af5:


    nar "If I can clear her mind of worry, even for just a moment, then my job here is done."


translate English day5_my_T_a787ad1d:


    my "Thank you."


translate English day5_my_T_60ae5cab:


    nar "She answers in a tone of voice I've heard before. {w}Maybe she's willing to overlook my sometimes desperate actions."


translate English day5_my_T_a7e48574:


    nar "It's enough that I find myself heaving a sigh that's a mix of both relief and joy. {w}The last thing I want right now is to lose her."


translate English day5_my_T_d7bb733c:


    nar "Maya honestly is a big help to me just from her mere presence alone."


translate English day5_my_T_21c70d38:


    nar "Before heading back to our dorms, we turn from the main corridor and pause for a moment in the garden."


translate English day5_my_T_42f2e5d1:


    nar "I'm sure Maya's hometown had far more flowers than here--my village certainly did."


translate English day5_my_T_5828fb05:


    nar "And we probably don't even have to go that far to find an abundance of flowers and other plant life. We'd just have to step outside the temple gates."


translate English day5_my_T_aef99cf5:


    nar "I want to go out there sometime with her. {w}It's the first dream I've ever held that I cannot accomplish by myself."


translate English day5_my_T_029fa68c:


    pl "The buds seem bigger compared to the last time I saw them."


translate English day5_my_T_79b4a8f7:


    my "They won't get too big overnight... They need time to grow."


translate English day5_my_T_cce4a095:


    pl "If you keep nurturing them everyday like I know you do, I'm sure they'll blossom beautifully before too long."


translate English day5_my_T_d23c88f0:


    my "I hope so..."


translate English day5_my_T_d6e1a0bc:


    pl "Maya, if we ever get some time off for a job well done, would you go on a trip somewhere with me?"


translate English day5_my_T_7247aa22:


    my "Do you think we'll ever get time off?"


translate English day5_my_T_399d18e1:


    pl "Of course we will! And the world outside of these walls is huge, full of so many birds and a colorful rainbow of all types of flowers. Wanna see them?"


translate English day5_my_T_28b1c528:


    my "I'm not sure if it's possible... {w}but it would definitely be a nice change of pace."


translate English day5_my_T_87482d64:


    pl "Exactly! The first time is accumulating a bunch of days off."


translate English day5_my_T_72182a92:


    nar "We are, without a doubt, struggling through the worst of it. {w}Even if our dreams are futile, as long as we have something to cling to that will motivate us to keep moving, {w}we can worry about the future later."


translate English day5_my_T_92b17d58:


    nar "And if we run into a similar problem, then we can come up with something new to dream about."


translate English day5_my_T_dbd93b82:


    nar "Rinse, wash, and repeat: then Maya will stay with me forever."


translate English day5_my_T_8a154c49:


    nar "That thought alone should have cheered me up, but all I can feel right now is bone-chilling exhaustion, most likely thanks to the events of the day."


translate English day5_cr_T_d4186278:



    nvl clear
    br "\n As everyone here knows, her hobby is collecting every rumor she can from throughout the temple. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_cr_T_b9f56b83:


    extend "\nSometimes she also takes the information that comes to her and creates a rumor out of it, which is mildly infuriating.{w} With the intent to tease her a little about it, {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_cr_T_01014cc0:


    extend "\nI've been listening in to her rumors for the last few days, but I barely get anything out of it.{w} At first, I was simply disappointed. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_cr_T_993114f4:


    extend "\n The only things the priests know about her are superficial--things I already know about. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_cr_T_35e7fa40:


    extend "\nBut then a thought occurred to me. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_cr_T_c1630d6a:


    extend "\nHow is it that even though she's incredibly interested in so many other people, they don't seem to have any interest in her?"


translate English day5_cr_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_cr_T_39a20fdc:


    nar "After leaving the infirmary, the first place that comes to mind is the stairwell."


translate English day5_cr_T_f13019c4:


    nar "Given that it's a central staircase leading from the front gates, it's essentially a little-used emergency stairwell at the moment."


translate English day5_cr_T_e10e7ac5:


    nar "Claire isn't here; I probably came too early.{w} Normally, the quiet in this dark and quiet place is comforting--now it's just tantalizing."


translate English day5_cr_T_e3c4dc99:


    nar "The shadows beyond the hallway wrapped in darkness have more depth to me today."


translate English day5_cr_T_88447234:


    nar "A chill runs down my spine.{w} That's not a thought I've ever had before."


translate English day5_cr_T_9e8cc1b5:


    nar "Is this sudden feeling just because I'm a little lonely since she's not here?"


translate English day5_cr_T_5b6bd3f3:


    nar "No--I can't say for certain this unease is just from loneliness.{w} What's going on in my head right now?"


translate English day5_cr_T_eb1e660c:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_cr_T_fcd71bd1:


    nar "I leave the quiet stairs and exit into the passage."


translate English day5_cr_T_dcf621f0:


    nar "At first I just walk around for a little bit.{w} But as I'm walking alone, for some reason I grow scared, and my steps quicken."


translate English day5_cr_T_0e78e2fc:


    nar "The silence that was once comforting now weighs heavy on me. Everyone else is at work or in their dorms right now."


translate English day5_cr_T_e3e0be05:


    nar "The lobby, always flooded with waves of people, is now as quiet as those stairs.{w} I walk through the wide passage by myself, then recall a certain voice."


translate English day5_cr_T_7fd6164e:


    nar "A bright voice, in contrast to this gloomy, depressing temple, that was all the more audible in quiet places."


translate English day5_cr_T_e8d7f9b7:


    nar "Her voice echoes around in my empty mind several times."


translate English day5_cr_T_61755d43:


    nar "During my aimless wanderings, I suddenly see a light in the dark hallway. It's coming from the infirmary."


translate English day5_cr_T_e65bfef1:


    nar "Remembering my conversation with her has led me here, whether I like it or not.{w} I glimpse a shadow here and there beyond the illuminated window."


translate English day5_cr_T_a97d694b:


    nar "As I stare, the door bursts open." with sshake


translate English day5_cr_T_bff5d264:


    gr "Oh! [na2], you've come."


translate English day5_cr_T_2d85f6ff:


    pl "Doctor!!! Don't scare me like that...!"


translate English day5_cr_T_7ba36504:


    gr "I'm sorry. That was a funny coincidence, wasn't it? How are you feeling?"


translate English day5_cr_T_06abc87e:


    pl "I got a good rest, thanks for asking. You're still on the job, right? Should you be in the infirmary?"


translate English day5_cr_T_0b8514e1:


    gr "Well, actually, we're having a bit of a problem..."


translate English day5_cr_T_9045c509:


    nar "Dr. Grette looks back into the still-lit infirmary.{w} I peer in as well, but it seems empty."


translate English day5_cr_T_9764558b:


    gr "Did you happen to see Claire on your way here, [na2]?"


translate English day5_cr_T_06de4a3a:


    pl "Claire?{w} Funny thing, I was looking for her myself. Did something happen?"


translate English day5_cr_T_fca46027:


    gr "It's just that before she left yesterday, she said she'd visit again today, but I haven't heard anything from her."


translate English day5_cr_T_19f7e42b:


    gr "Hmm, she's not the type to break her word..."


translate English day5_cr_T_1343a76b:


    pl "Claire..."


translate English day5_cr_T_5c0b549d:


    gr "I know you're probably really tired right now, but would you mind alphabetizing the papers on the desk over there?"


translate English day5_cr_T_08024d65:


    gr "Normally she's the one who does it and I'm in a big hurry right now.{w} But if it's too much for you, you don't have to push yourself."


translate English day5_cr_T_36fd4b80:


    pl "Hmm. I think I can handle that much. I'm not busy or anything.{w} Claire definitely said she'd come by today, right?"


translate English day5_cr_T_af6313e9:


    gr "Yes. Something must have come up. I'll try my best to get in contact with her for now, but...{w} Anyway, if she comes here, tell me, alright?"


translate English day5_cr_T_5f1294c4:


    gr "And if anything happens to you, [na2], go straight to the ward!"


translate English day5_cr_T_efe47d6c:


    pl "Okay, okay. I hope you find her, Doctor."


translate English day5_cr_T_307c60de:


    "\n I hear the pitter-patter of slippers slapping on the floor as she runs down the hall."


translate English day5_cr_T_52c4eaca:


    "Now I really am the last one left here."


translate English day5_cr_T_5e8738f3:


    "I remember the infirmary always having a warmth to it, with the scents of tea and sweets drifting through the air."


translate English day5_cr_T_b9e9931e:


    "But today that comforting air is gone--possibly because there haven't been many people coming in and out."


translate English day5_cr_T_fbe14ee6:


    "Or maybe it's because the ever-present Dr. Grette left.{w} Come to think of it, the whole Health Department has seemed really busy all day."


translate English day5_cr_T_b1b38e69:


    et "And I'm pretty sure I'm the cause of it."


translate English day5_cr_T_e0885d05:



    nvl clear
    "\n There aren't many documents in folders on the desk."


translate English day5_cr_T_e10274a0:


    "It's child's play compared to the piles and piles of them on the Cleanup Department desks."


translate English day5_cr_T_e6c67198:


    "I need to alphabetize them all. Looking at them, most of the folders have someone's name on it."


translate English day5_cr_T_0d81ec24:


    "As I'm sorting the documents marked with unfamiliar names into folders, I come across a more familiar name."


translate English day5_cr_T_0ab5920d:


    "Clione Myosotis...{w} That's Claire's name.{w} Are these some sort of records of Health Department priests?"


translate English day5_cr_T_ecfd6c78:


    et "I know I shouldn't open her file up without asking, but my hands move before my mind can stop them. I tell myself it's to help figure out where she is right now."


translate English day5_cr_T_a7efee06:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Wait. What is this?\""


translate English day5_cr_T_4f194032:


    "The words come out accidentally.{w} That's how strange the contents of the file are."


translate English day5_cr_T_ba47e409:


    "Underneath a heading that says \"Counseling Record\" is a table containing personal information."


translate English day5_cr_T_8e1712ed:


    "Since Dr. Grette is not only the auxiliary bishop of the Health Department but also a counselor, these documents are probably in relation to that."


translate English day5_cr_T_776b7c67:


    "Leaving this task in the hands of an outsider must show how much she trusts me."


translate English day5_cr_T_0e96f1c0:


    et "But I've already read the contents--simply due to my carelessness."


translate English day5_cr_T_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_cr_T_53065d24:


    "\n Everything written below the name I knew was completely new to me."


translate English day5_cr_T_69ef9930:


    "Apparently, she has a much older fiance--about thirty years older--and is regularly abused by him."


translate English day5_cr_T_9169f32e:


    "The words on the page are unimaginable, and quickly have me feeling rattled.{w} Is it okay for me to even know about this stuff?"


translate English day5_cr_T_e2942ab9:


    "I want to close this file right now and go back to my normal life, but I know it's too late after reading that first sentence."


translate English day5_cr_T_1c2a566b:


    et "She is generally forbidden from eating anything while he is watching."


translate English day5_cr_T_16f77806:



    "\n He makes her take baths for two hours straight to make sure she's perfectly clean, but that's simply water torture that they call 'bathing'."


translate English day5_cr_T_7bfc1a7d:


    "He ties her wrists with hose and leaves her like that, and shuts her in dark places like a wardrobe under the bed to treat her like she's not even there."


translate English day5_cr_T_d3b150c8:


    "He dehumanizes both her and her parents with words, of course, but also enacts more direct physical violence against her like throwing sharp objects at her. But he purposely never strikes her in the face."


translate English day5_cr_T_6dda8c54:


    "And if she does receive a facial injury, he forces her to dunk her head in a basin filled with ice water to force the swelling to recede."


translate English day5_cr_T_3a943c08:


    et "Whenever they argue, he uses weapons--blades, hammers, and the like--to threaten her into submission."


translate English day5_cr_T_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_cr_T_44182ccf:


    "\n \"Damn it... Damn it all!\"" with sshake


translate English day5_cr_T_49bd19a7:


    "Each of the thirty-one counseling sessions recorded her tell me something equally shocking, but my mind steadily starts to white out."


translate English day5_cr_T_138c9c5c:


    "Maybe that's why my hands start to frantically search around the desk."


translate English day5_cr_T_f4d79933:


    "Does everyone from the Health Department know about this? If they do, why aren't they doing anything about it?{w} They should have at least been able to do something more than I could ever do..."


translate English day5_cr_T_fe454a50:


    "I thought they were simple and good people, but they were definitely the worst out of all the adults I'd met.{w} I can't believe they have the gall to call themselves priests of the Health Department and perform counseling and treatment on children!"


translate English day5_cr_T_49dbcb3c:


    et "Haven't I just found recorded proof of that? Me, an outsider?"


translate English day5_cr_T_1f6806bc:



    nvl clear
    "\n The wounds vary in when they happen and how long they take to heal and are focused mainly on the side, the inner arm, and the inner thigh."


translate English day5_cr_T_e8d46344:


    "Aside from the externally visible wounds, she has burn marks indicative of tobacco and scalding,"


translate English day5_cr_T_01cef68d:


    extend " a scalp hematoma from ripped hair, and she claims to have light headaches and dizziness whenever she blinks or walks around."


translate English day5_cr_T_023cc182:


    "I don't need to read much further to understand what kind a life Claire has lived."


translate English day5_cr_T_e8824a8d:


    "The Claire I know is a bright, cheerful, slightly mischief-loving rich princess filled with naive curiosity."


translate English day5_cr_T_ba5ef78e:


    et "I knew she was hiding something behind all that, but I never pried that deeply."


translate English day5_cr_T_2ea39152:



    nvl clear
    "\n It looks like I've been under a grave misunderstanding."


translate English day5_cr_T_18a37691:


    "A vague misconception that I was the only one who could save her--that I was the only one whose saving she needed."


translate English day5_cr_T_ed4ba4ba:


    et "But with it all laid bare like this, I realize there's nothing at all I can do. Not one damn thing."


translate English day5_cr_T_31c8f8b5:



    nvl clear
    "\n Just as Claire is an outsider to the temple, I'm an outsider to her family situation."


translate English day5_cr_T_b5ac990b:


    "And I didn't even hear about any of this from her."


translate English day5_cr_T_83c9d437:


    "I snuck a peek at her counseling records, which she believes are safely confidential."


translate English day5_cr_T_5aa961cb:


    "She's never asked me for help. Not even once."


translate English day5_cr_T_c0187e86:


    "Until now, if she got mixed up in trouble with others, I could just comfort her a little or offer her simple help to resolve the situation."


translate English day5_cr_T_09220c83:


    "But for this, I have no idea what to even say, much less how to help out.{w} Without meaning to, I heave a sigh."


translate English day5_cr_T_9c34886d:


    et "I wrack my brain, but it's too complicated for me to come up with anything."


translate English day5_cr_T_76b2fe88_3:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_cr_T_f89e660d:


    nar "I start to hear footsteps in the distance.{w} They're not Grette's though."


translate English day5_cr_T_09992ab1:


    nar "These are shoes with heels. The steps are quick and short, running down the hallway as if to leave everything else behind--and they sound precarious enough that the owner could fall over at any moment."


translate English day5_cr_T_a5880269:


    nar "The sound quickly approaches."


translate English day5_cr_T_86da851e:


    cr "......!"


translate English day5_cr_T_4195ae87:


    nar "A small figure appears in the left-open doorway.{w} I know exactly who it is, of course."


translate English day5_cr_T_fa4a3dfd:


    nar "Because she'd never break a promise with an adult."


translate English day5_cr_T_d8a49f58:


    cr "Lord [na]! What are you doing here?"


translate English day5_cr_T_f757468d:


    nar "Claire catches her breath, one hand grasping the string of a light bag probably carrying a few possessions."


translate English day5_cr_T_8acf9267:


    nar "I close the file; I don't need to read any further.{w} I have to talk to her the same way I always do."


translate English day5_cr_T_fecf5559:


    pl "You're a little late, aren't you? I thought you promised Dr. Grette you'd be coming. She was worried about you!"


translate English day5_cr_T_d12ed4d8:


    cr "Oh! I actually had something urgent come up...{w} What should I do? Where did Lady Grette go?"


translate English day5_cr_T_444c1231:


    pl "She should be here soon, so you can probably just wait here."


translate English day5_cr_T_4d92b851:


    pl "Plus, I got all the work done that our troublesome little truant couldn't do."


translate English day5_cr_T_85674812:


    cr "Well goodness, I'm very grateful!{w} But I am *not* troublesome! Something really did come up that I couldn't get out of."


translate English day5_cr_T_e4ad8f29:


    cr "Also, I wasn't even scheduled to visit at all today! If you follow everything back, then it was you, Lord [na], that--"


translate English day5_cr_T_1b83db97:


    pl "Did it have to do with family stuff?"


translate English day5_cr_T_ba7e5d9d:


    cr "It did indeed. My visitation was stubbornly opposed, as I have a very important matter to take care of tomorrow."


translate English day5_cr_T_7e6ff870:


    cr "Oh! Did I tell you? I'm actually engaged to someone!"


translate English day5_cr_T_2f17eeff:


    pl "Wow, you never told me that."


translate English day5_cr_T_e5ede484:


    cr "Of course I didn't. I wanted to see your jaw drop in genuine surprise!"


translate English day5_cr_T_0ea96e1d:


    cr "Heh heh heh... Why would a cute girl like me NOT have a man?{w} Unfortunate for you, huh? I'm sure it comes as quite the shock!"


translate English day5_cr_T_f3d06518:


    pl "Why didn't you tell me that sooner?!" with sshake


translate English day5_cr_T_5093ec0d:


    nar "For a moment, everything fell silent.{w} Even Claire, who always spoke with such pep and energy, blinked at me, unable to continue."


translate English day5_cr_T_8a9ed738:


    nar "The conversation comes to a stop and the air in the infirmary turns just as cold. After my thoughtless outburst, only my heartbeat pounds annoyingly in my ears."


translate English day5_cr_T_e2c486de:


    cr "Lord [na]..."


translate English day5_cr_T_f0f5fa9c:


    pl "And let me apologize up front. I saw your counseling records."


translate English day5_cr_T_09c5e82e:


    cr "Oh, my! You went fishing around in a lady's private information?"


translate English day5_cr_T_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_cr_T_62e1a68d:


    cr "Well... I suppose it doesn't matter.{w} There's quite an age gap between him and I and our opinions are often...at odds."


translate English day5_cr_T_186a3678:


    cr "I asked Lady Grette for counseling because I thought she might know a lot about couple's conflicts."


translate English day5_cr_T_d7668b9d:


    cr "I'm rather embarrassed to have been outed as a woman who can't properly perform her wifely duties."


translate English day5_cr_T_0a6ff967:


    pl "I don't think you could call him abusing you a \"conflict.\"{w} You're just under fire from that guy's grubby violence!"


translate English day5_cr_T_d41f74be:


    cr "Grubby? That's an awful way to put it."


translate English day5_cr_T_317b4898:


    pl "How else am I supposed to describe a man who has a much younger girl in the palm of his hand AND hurts her?"


translate English day5_cr_T_6abc6d9c:


    pl "I can't believe your parents even allowed their daughter to be engaged to that crazy madman. Can't they see that you're hurting?!"


translate English day5_cr_T_75adba0d:


    pl "Makes me wonder which is more rotten--their eyes or their brains."


translate English day5_cr_T_4e493f2a:


    cr "Hey! Don't you think bringing my parents into this is overstepping things?!"


translate English day5_cr_T_d07ba2e6:


    cr "Have you ever once met my parents or my fiance, Lord [na]?"


translate English day5_cr_T_add725fe:


    cr "You only came to these biased conclusions because all you did was steal a look at my private counseling records."


translate English day5_cr_T_4df9672c:


    cr "Do you understand how rude you're being right now?"


translate English day5_cr_T_bf1e8e37:


    pl "I don't care how it NORMALLY is or ACTUALLY is or whatever!!!"


translate English day5_cr_T_7f4910a7:


    pl "The important thing is how that man is beating and abusing you."


translate English day5_cr_T_1de0ba03:


    pl "You just don't understand how messed up that is because you're still a kid!"


translate English day5_cr_T_43515c00:


    cr "That's what I'm saying is so rude of you! I would thank you not to make idle guesses about my life outside the temple!"


translate English day5_cr_T_29e90565:


    cr "If you only look at the fact that he raises his hand against me, then yes.{w} Perhaps it does look bad."


translate English day5_cr_T_94d5fb1a:


    cr "But he's only punishing me in a way that suits the wrongs I commit!"


translate English day5_cr_T_5ecedfc8:


    pl "Wrongs? Yeah, like what? Talking about stuff he doesn't care about?"


translate English day5_cr_T_87d33e28:


    pl "Throwing a fit over wanting to come to the temple? Eating your food earlier, even though it's not mealtime?"


translate English day5_cr_T_d90e51b0:


    pl "No matter what the situation is, nobody with any sense would be violent with you for it!"


translate English day5_cr_T_9124ecd0:


    cr "Please, stop this!{w} He is soon to become my husband, and I love him from the bottom of my heart!" with sshake


translate English day5_cr_T_ebdeaea0:


    nar "Each time I take a step forward, Claire takes one back.{w} I raise my hand at her--and she shrieks, putting her slender arms up to cover her head."


translate English day5_cr_T_99dfed0d:


    nar "Her eyes are shut tightly, and they're trembling."


translate English day5_cr_T_609f7784:


    nar "When I look closer, it's not only her eyes. Under the shadow that is so much larger than her body, she's shaking all over."


translate English day5_cr_T_9c3a8d1a:


    pl "...If that was true, you wouldn't have reacted like that."


translate English day5_cr_T_38963584:


    nar "I put my hand back down.{w} Claire slowly opens her eyes and straightens up, then looks at her own trembling hands."


translate English day5_cr_T_fa4492fd:


    nar "And then she raise her hands over her complicated head, looking up at them--again, in surprise. Her well-combed aqua blue hair is now ruffled."


translate English day5_cr_T_fb119b6f:


    cr "That was, well... I was simply startled, and...!"


translate English day5_cr_T_ef30754a:


    pl "Give some thought as to how you look right now.{w} You're a smart girl, Claire."


translate English day5_cr_T_15c476f4:


    cr "......"


translate English day5_cr_T_209ce80e:


    pl "Nobody who truly loved you would ever do such a horrible thing to you."


translate English day5_cr_T_9a0dbc77:


    pl "And if you had your head on straight, you'd never seriously love him either..."


translate English day5_cr_T_e180841c:


    cr "But... Well, my father, and my mother, they--"


translate English day5_cr_T_23943d0b:


    pl "Be realistic. It's your parents' fault you think that way, but it's not what YOU really think, is it?"


translate English day5_cr_T_3daacf71:


    cr "What I think...?"


translate English day5_cr_T_ee5fc0f5:


    nar "Claire falls into thought.{w} Her bag still hangs from her shoulder; she hasn't put it down yet."


translate English day5_cr_T_ec73c218:


    cr "Is there truly no emotion between us?"


translate English day5_cr_T_494d29c4:


    pl "Even if there was, it'd have a bad effect on you for sure, not a good one."


translate English day5_cr_T_ee176d9a:


    pl "You didn't even know your fianc√© until your parents stuck you with the guy, did you, Claire?"


translate English day5_cr_T_b2385e66:


    cr "I...I didn't.{w} I don't even know him very well now."


translate English day5_cr_T_36265ee9:


    cr "Especially since it seems he doesn't particularly care for my annoying conversation."


translate English day5_cr_T_775069d1:


    pl "Has nobody ever taught you that's wrong?"


translate English day5_cr_T_47e32874:


    cr "...Lady Grette and the Health Department bishop have always worried about me.{w} But I suppose I never considered what the cause of their worries was."


translate English day5_cr_T_a788850f:


    cr "I'm still too young to actually marry, and I'm fairly scatterbrained.{w} You were the first one, Lord [na]."


translate English day5_cr_T_ec3ac527:


    pl "I really doubt I was the first...{w} It's just that you couldn't accept how grave your situation is before."


translate English day5_cr_T_94213292:


    pl "I know I'm just one of many when I say this, but I'm worried sick about you."


translate English day5_cr_T_fe53a5bb:


    pl "So worried I'd do just about anything if it would help you at all."


translate English day5_cr_T_96efd04b:


    cr "Lord [na]..."


translate English day5_cr_T_d458b2f1:


    nar "Once again, I hear the footfalls of slippers.{w} The sound tells me that the discussion is over."


translate English day5_cr_T_b7f147c7:


    nar "I take a few steps away from Claire, and after a long look at me, she turns her eyes elsewhere."


translate English day5_cr_T_f598bb09:


    nar "The newcomer, who rushed back more quickly than normal, broke into a smile upon seeing Claire."


translate English day5_cr_T_231ad614:


    gr "Claire! You're here. I was so worried! Is everything alright?"


translate English day5_cr_T_48c20543:


    cr "Lady Grette! I'm sorry for not contacting you."


translate English day5_cr_T_167c631c:


    gr "It's fine! Don't worry about it. Are you alright? Did you get here fine?"


translate English day5_cr_T_e0375616:


    cr "I did. I simply had to talk about tomorrow's plans for a short while. I'm sorry for worrying you."


translate English day5_cr_T_3b1447d7:


    gr "Thank goodness. I really was worried about you..."


translate English day5_cr_T_c35a8073:


    nar "Grette is either just trying to meet Claire's eyes or get a closer inspection of her."


translate English day5_cr_T_1c28b00f:


    nar "She stays bent over a bit as she asks Claire the same \"are you alright\" question several times. Finally, she breathes a sigh of relief."


translate English day5_cr_T_841880d9:


    nar "Just as I'm about to retreat out of sight, Claire's gaze stops on me and I freeze in place."


translate English day5_cr_T_1f658490:


    nar "She finally straightens up and faces me."


translate English day5_cr_T_70ab9100:


    gr "Thank you so much, [na2]. I'm sorry for making you do this when you must be exhausted."


translate English day5_cr_T_75dafba6:


    pl "I was looking for Claire anyway, so don't worry about it. And it was an easy job."


translate English day5_cr_T_3c2b4eb1:


    gr "Are you two friends?"


translate English day5_cr_T_eb43fb7d:


    nar "For once, I can't answer right away. Without meaning to, I look at Claire.{w} Unfortunately, she seems to feel the same way."


translate English day5_cr_T_d42fa2bf:


    nar "She looks at me at the same time, so our eyes abruptly meet."


translate English day5_cr_T_2f3be374:


    nar "To me, Claire is..."


translate English day5_cr_T_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_cr_T_fafcaa21:


    "{nw}"


translate English day5_cr_T_515e2753:


    cr "Of course! We're the best of buddies!"


translate English day5_cr_T_7f1a3e7d:


    nar "Claire answers first.{w} Hearing her call us best buddies gives me a sense of nervous satisfaction."


translate English day5_cr_T_5a6fd7b4:


    pl "Right. We know more about each other than anyone else, after all."


translate English day5_cr_T_d20936f4:


    nar "Compared to Grette, who smiles and nods, Claire seems surprised for some reason."


translate English day5_cr_T_7d14883d:


    gr "Hee hee hee. I'm glad you're such good friends. It makes me happy."


translate English day5_cr_T_946dbef2:


    gr "And while I would very much like for us all to have some tea..."


translate English day5_cr_T_dd29965c:


    cr "...?"


translate English day5_cr_T_54655596:


    gr "Claire, when I called earlier, I received a message.{w} Your parents need to talk with you as soon as possible."


translate English day5_cr_T_dceabe46:


    cr "They do?"


translate English day5_cr_T_eb1e660c_3:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_cr_T_f7513ab4:


    gr "They're coming to pick you up as you speak. Will you be alright?"


translate English day5_cr_T_3e80986a:


    nar "Those words aren't meant just for Claire.{w} She's asking me, too."


translate English day5_cr_T_76f28b1e:


    nar "Claire picks up on that fact herself, and just like before, pauses before answering.{w} Our eyes quickly meet again."


translate English day5_cr_T_43e9c96d:


    nar "For no particular reason, I look past the dark doorway. Then I ask her a question."


translate English day5_cr_T_34aee1f0:


    pl "Claire, will you be able to come in tomorrow?"


translate English day5_cr_T_51437abf:


    cr "I cannot rightly say, though I'd very much like to, if I'm able."


translate English day5_cr_T_11060b8c:


    pl "Hey, if you want to come in, come in.{w} I don't know what other stuff you have going on, but I'll be waiting for you."


translate English day5_cr_T_747a48f8:


    cr "Please, don't wait for me! There's no guarantee I'll be here."


translate English day5_cr_T_53f0f335:


    pl "You've gotta have more confidence when you make a promise.{w} Right, Doctor?"


translate English day5_cr_T_9170b9c4:


    gr "...[na2] is right, Claire."


translate English day5_cr_T_2b80ebc5:


    gr "You can have all the time you need to think about how things will turn out later, but would you tell me what it is you want to do right now?"


translate English day5_cr_T_15c476f4_1:


    cr "......"


translate English day5_cr_T_f1713d39:


    cr "Yes... I'll be sure to come in tomorrow."


translate English day5_cr_T_e904943c:


    nar "I nod.{w} This resolves nothing, but for some reason, I feel like things will go well in the future, no matter what happens."


translate English day5_cr_T_ed10196a:


    nar "The reason being the hopeful tone in her answer, one that I've never heard from her before."


translate English day5_cr_T_07c86c1c:


    nar "I still don't know what Claire acknowledging her problems will result in."


translate English day5_cr_T_6a8ad49f:


    nar "But I'm confident I can help her whenever she needs it."


translate English day5_cr_T_cadb3e3c:


    nar "And for today, that's enough."


translate English day5_hk_T_89dde9d9:


    br "\n That she can stand before us every morning, her laid-back personality in direct contrast with her impeccable work ethic, dressed in a freshly ironed habit,{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_hk_T_179ddb87:


    extend "\nher hair brushed back into a neat ponytail without even one strand out of place, is testament to her exceptional and bewitching beauty.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_hk_T_f713287b:


    extend "\nThough I guess it's really all thanks to Securett Rafe.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_hk_T_7c3a7bb9:


    extend "\nHe might be moody and tends to take things overly seriously, but when push comes to shove and the bishop becomes the target of whatever inevitable act of violence is thrown our way, {w}rumor has it that Securett bears the brunt of it in her place."


translate English day5_hk_T_795c8dee:



    nvl clear
    br "\n Though I believe it's mostly rumors born from his unfortunate countenance, seemingly at odds with the bishop's own beauty.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_hk_T_0c2a8a1b:


    extend "\nThough it wouldn't surprise me if it were true, knowing how utterly enchanting she can be."


translate English day5_hk_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_hk_T_b60dd7f2:


    nar "I drag my leaden legs toward the workplace. {w}Considering the unfortunate events of the day, I'm not entirely convinced going to see the bishop now is a good idea."


translate English day5_hk_T_ce8021c7:


    nar "I'll probably only be a distraction, in which case the only thing I'll end up getting is a firm talking to."


translate English day5_hk_T_8cd5614c:


    nar "And yet, I continue heading toward the workplace anyway. {w}Not with any particular purpose in mind, I think to myself."


translate English day5_hk_T_d7e4b5b2:


    nar "It almost feels like I'm being led there by some unknown force, my legs moving of their own free will."


translate English day5_hk_T_352468be:


    nar "With my thoughts scattered and fuzzy, I struggle with the uncomfortable feeling that my gravely injured arm is no longer attached to my body."


translate English day5_hk_T_637fe728:


    nar "I wonder how the bishop will react when she sees me."


translate English day5_hk_T_e4fec13b:


    nar "The all too selfish wish that I could have stayed seriously injured briefly crosses my mind, probably brought about due to how quickly I was healed."


translate English day5_hk_T_e4b26a87:


    nar "My pain and the fear I felt alongside it are both gone. {w}It was just this afternoon, and yet it's still hard for me to believe I was actually on the brink of losing my life."


translate English day5_hk_T_c69aeb10:


    pl "Oh!!!"


translate English day5_hk_T_6cd20f98:


    nar "I always seem to bump into him. Seeing his face shocks a startled yelp from my lips."


translate English day5_hk_T_e3efe6d7:


    nar "His own lips are slightly parted, as if I startled a similar cry of surprise out of him. Usually his mouth is kept tightly shut."


translate English day5_hk_T_83613f09:


    nar "And yet no sound comes out, which only deepens the silence between us. Infinitely more awkward than usual."


translate English day5_hk_T_93ab03b2:


    nar "I woke up hating his guts, though my strong dislike for him has dulled significantly since his apology."


translate English day5_hk_T_7ed49113:


    sc "Going to see the bishop?"


translate English day5_hk_T_15fe4b7e:


    nar "He seems to be judging the new interpersonal distance between us. His voice sounds less hollow than usual."


translate English day5_hk_T_bf01eb4b:


    pl "Maybe. Busy with work?"


translate English day5_hk_T_1821006e:


    sc "...Yeah."


translate English day5_hk_T_346c1449:


    nar "I appreciated our talk earlier, though I have no desire to let this conversation go any further."


translate English day5_hk_T_ab6d5b26:


    nar "Just as I attempt to walk away, Securett resumes talking to me."


translate English day5_hk_T_5d2230a6:


    sc "Hold on, there's something I need to say."


translate English day5_hk_T_638638f4:


    pl "You need something? From me?"


translate English day5_hk_T_70203cc7:


    sc "It'll just take a second. {w}Don't worry, I have no desire to keep you here longer than need be."


translate English day5_hk_T_a73df934:


    sc "Plus, I doubt the bishop will be going anywhere anytime soon."


translate English day5_hk_T_8a08639c:


    pl "Okay..."


translate English day5_hk_T_1a6fa7d3:


    nar "I'm still suspicious, but I lead us over to a nearby wall."


translate English day5_hk_T_5876ff24:


    nar "The folks around here are already on edge, and I don't want to cast further doubt onto him than there already is."


translate English day5_hk_T_7de58907:


    nar "From up close, his unevenly cut hair looks like chopped up lettuce."


translate English day5_hk_T_630a91ba:


    nar "He brushes his bangs to the opposite side of his head from me, as if deep in thought over what he wants to say."


translate English day5_hk_T_184f773a:


    nar "A part of me wants to ask where he gets his hair cut, but knowing he'll say something like, \"that place next to the dorms,\" I decide to keep my mouth shut."


translate English day5_hk_T_bf17979f:


    sc "I know this might sound weird, but..."


translate English day5_hk_T_508c333b:


    pl "Hm?"


translate English day5_hk_T_9a43e8e2:


    sc "...I had a strange thought."


translate English day5_hk_T_a337f636:


    pl "I don't think that's strange at all. What's going on?"


translate English day5_hk_T_8dba02fd:


    sc "Do you ever get an uncomfortable feeling when you talk to Haku... er, to the bishop?"


translate English day5_hk_T_0b0c9488:


    pl "Are you really about to bad-mouth her again?"


translate English day5_hk_T_fecd23b7:


    sc "No, I'm just curious about something."


translate English day5_hk_T_5c2e8588:


    pl "I don't feel uncomfortable at all when I talk to her."


translate English day5_hk_T_1d6567d4:


    nar "That's not a lie. {w}Though I do get weird vibes from her appearance and her general existence, our conversations in and of themselves are fairly ordinary."


translate English day5_hk_T_0a537597:


    sc "I see..."


translate English day5_hk_T_d94d988c:


    nar "He peers at me suspiciously for a moment, as if doubting my answer, before nodding in acceptance."


translate English day5_hk_T_4161ce18:


    sc "The bishop mentioned you. {w}She thinks highly of you. She said something about how much she enjoys talking with you."


translate English day5_hk_T_49051913:


    pl "She really said that?"


translate English day5_hk_T_f0c7041e:


    sc "Which is what made me curious to begin with. Are you trying to get closer to her for some reason?"


translate English day5_hk_T_19a17e02:


    sc "Or are you simply attempting to curry favor?"


translate English day5_hk_T_5c7255e2:


    pl "What does it matter? Why do you need to know?"


translate English day5_hk_T_d70ff4af:


    sc "She likes a great number of people, but doesn't tend to keep them around."


translate English day5_hk_T_92be46c1:


    sc "I mean, she is usually surrounded by a number of folks, but you know that's not what I meant."


translate English day5_hk_T_ffbed78f:


    pl "Yeah."


translate English day5_hk_T_f90e337b:


    sc "To be honest, I'm glad that she has someone with whom she feels comfortable talking to."


translate English day5_hk_T_0eb46589:


    pl "Then your actions up until now make no sense whatsoever."


translate English day5_hk_T_2757762d:


    sc "I'm sure you're aware of this on some level, right? She's the type of person you must be very, very careful around."


translate English day5_hk_T_11bfd35f:


    sc "Thanks to her innocence, she is far more sensitive than anyone else here in the temple. {w}Meaning she is far more susceptible to get hurt if one were to force the wrong kind of attention on her."


translate English day5_hk_T_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day5_hk_T_005f795d:


    sc "And while she can be easily hurt at any time, she can easily hurt others without warning."


translate English day5_hk_T_75d9a336:


    sc "I'm not sure if she comes off as perfect or flawed in your eyes, but she is exactly the way she is supposed to be."


translate English day5_hk_T_c05c53d3:


    sc "What I'm trying to say is she will never change from how she is now... {w}No matter what."


translate English day5_hk_T_5ece7c11:


    nar "At first glance, his warning sounds the same as always, though after the events of today, it takes on a slightly different meaning."


translate English day5_hk_T_0cf7ae8e:


    nar "Up until now, he's been worried about her and wary of me. {w}That much is undoubtedly true."


translate English day5_hk_T_7fda9a1e:


    nar "But based on what he just said, it's clear that he's not just wary of me anymore."


translate English day5_hk_T_285430b0:


    nar "He's *worried* about me as well."


translate English day5_hk_T_a6022112:


    pl "There's no way I would have ever come to such a hasty decision in front of those people."


translate English day5_hk_T_9b33e05b:


    nar "I'm sure Securett meant that in response to his internal distress, but they weigh heavily on my own heart. {w}Honestly, I'm not confident enough to say the opposite is true."


translate English day5_hk_T_5c1fffc1:


    nar "I've outwardly doubted her a multitude of times. {w}And most likely hurt her in the process."


translate English day5_hk_T_551144a5:


    nar "Feeling slightly ashamed at my past actions, I can't bring myself to look him in the face."


translate English day5_hk_T_b4db7bb2:


    sc "It's exactly like I said on day one. You might hear her talk about some strange things... {w}but what you do with that is up to you."


translate English day5_hk_T_0b6ed57e:


    pl "I'm surprised to hear you say that. I got the impression that you hated Haku this whole time."


translate English day5_hk_T_00165cb4:


    sc "Is that what people are saying?"


translate English day5_hk_T_bef8a155:


    pl "Well..."


translate English day5_hk_T_1ca3525a:


    sc "I've never spoken even a single word of hate toward the bishop. {w}Instead of trying to formulate your own version of the truth, it's much better to simply talk to the person in question."


translate English day5_hk_T_7138d457:


    pl "Then why didn't you say anything earlier?"


translate English day5_hk_T_c56c8aa6:


    sc "The folks who work on the Disposal Team don't care about facts. They just want to gossip about whatever the most interesting topic of the week is."


translate English day5_hk_T_ff448692:


    sc "Stepping in to correct these rumors is basically like adding fuel to the flames."


translate English day5_hk_T_fd9ecc3b:


    sc "And it'll probably only make things worse..."


translate English day5_hk_T_0282633d:


    sc "Such a counterproductive action will only end up backfiring and harming the bishop. {w}In the end, people are all the same, whether they exist inside or outside of the temple."


translate English day5_hk_T_ca3dcab0:


    pl "Ignorance is bliss... as they say."


translate English day5_hk_T_da751ed0:


    pl "Still, you could have easily been nothing more than a yes man and she would have been equally as pleased. {w}Though I'm not denying how happy she is with you."


translate English day5_hk_T_52008b09:


    pl "What do you two normally talk about anyway?"


translate English day5_hk_T_b5e49886:


    sc "Nothing special..."


translate English day5_hk_T_d5ecac80:


    pl "Hrm? And yet the two of you seem as thick as thieves for having nothing special to talk about."


translate English day5_hk_T_4f611ed2:


    sc "We chat about trivial things, like the weather or the meal for the day... Just meaningless, everyday stuff."


translate English day5_hk_T_294a63a4:


    sc "She doesn't talk to me about any of that stuff. {w}And I'm the official \"temporary\" auxiliary bishop, too..."


translate English day5_hk_T_7f02ef6a:


    nar "If he's the auxiliary bishop, then why bother specifying the temporary part?"


translate English day5_hk_T_4bb1da4d:


    nar "My memory of him working frantically in the Workplace flits through my mind. {w}The sensitive and always moody temporary auxiliary bishop of the Cleanup Department..."


translate English day5_hk_T_942308e5:


    nar "The shade thrown by a mysterious individual was enough to keep him getting promoted, though I get the feeling he'd prefer to be recognized on his own merits."


translate English day5_hk_T_04285ee1:


    sc "At any rate, she is our bishop. {w}And my job as auxiliary bishop is to support her. That's the only thing that matters."


translate English day5_hk_T_07d21112:


    pl "Is that the reason why we had to have this conversation?"


translate English day5_hk_T_67232753:


    sc "It is... That's all I wanted to say. {w}I'm sorry for taking up your time. You can go."


translate English day5_hk_T_630df22a:


    pl "Keep working hard."


translate English day5_hk_T_a7ef7575:


    nar "Each deep breath forces the musky, putrid air inside your body, filling your stomach cavity. Looking in from the entrance, the Workplace seems tragically crushed underneath the dank, depressing sky."


translate English day5_hk_T_49b502a5:


    nar "The smoke from the incinerator is too heavy to dissipate into the atmosphere, instead floating just above the floor like a ghost, reminiscent of fog."


translate English day5_hk_T_34206b03:


    nar "Coughing thanks to the heavy shroud of smoke, I head toward the large warehouse. {w}This area always seems a bit more populated, although only just barely."


translate English day5_hk_T_ceec4bf6:


    nar "She stands in the shadows where no light can reach her. {w}And yet I'm able to easily spot her right away due to a flickering glow by her side."


translate English day5_hk_T_ad1647f7:


    nar "It's only a single candle, and yet the light feels exceptionally bright in the dark gloom of the warehouse."


translate English day5_hk_T_a4cbab4f:


    hk "Good morning."


translate English day5_hk_T_4b5894a5:


    nar "Spotting me at about the same time, she slowly walks over. I hang my head as she draws near, unable to look her in the face."


translate English day5_hk_T_6f4ee680:


    nar "Noticing specks of soot on the glass of the lantern, I wonder if it's a communal object."


translate English day5_hk_T_8d3ba36d:


    nar "My thoughts are interrupted by an unfamiliar sensation on both my cheeks. {w}It's the cool, smooth touch of her skin on mine."


translate English day5_hk_T_7808de0e:


    nar "The gentle pressure is enough to snap me back to reality. {w}A golden glow flickers just in front of me."


translate English day5_hk_T_5b51a04a:


    hk "It's polite to look people in the eye when you talk to them."


translate English day5_hk_T_cb430086:


    nar "It's enough to startle an involuntary response from me. {w}I shake my head, my body too stiff to do anything else."


translate English day5_hk_T_3dc7d2b6:


    nar "The rigidness in my posture immediately dissipates as soon as she steps back, and I feel my heartbeat quicken in response."


translate English day5_hk_T_65689cac:


    nar "I can feel my blood being pumped throughout my entire body."


translate English day5_hk_T_3fa6831d:


    hk "There's no problems with your injury?"


translate English day5_hk_T_0a7d5f70:


    pl "No... Thanks to you."


translate English day5_hk_T_b0d44dc4:


    hk "I apologize for my carelessness. It's my job as your bishop to make sure that doesn't happen, and yet..."


translate English day5_hk_T_5887f116:


    pl "Y-You don't have to apologize!!! It was my careless action that caused this entire mess. In fact, you should be scolding me, not apologizing!"


translate English day5_hk_T_2735d353:


    hk "I should be scolding you, huh?"


translate English day5_hk_T_fb1434b8:


    nar "Her apparent bewilderment over what I said is a mannerism of hers that I simply don't understand."


translate English day5_hk_T_57113417:


    pl "I've been getting all kinds of unexpected apologies today, from the auxiliary bishop to the actual bishop."


translate English day5_hk_T_a799ff1e:


    hk "What happened is simply part of the job."


translate English day5_hk_T_04344bdc:


    hk "Being responsible for your education and training, your safety is in our hands, and thus it is also our fault if and when problems arise."


translate English day5_hk_T_15aa4de7:


    pl "Rgh! Securett told me a similar thing this morning, though it carries a different amount of weight coming directly from the bishop herself!"


translate English day5_hk_T_37bc016a:


    pl "Words only carry as much weight as the person who says them."


translate English day5_hk_T_066dbac9:


    hk "A fair amount of responsibility rests on your shoulders, Brother [na], meaning we must never forget every one of our actions also reflects on our fellow priests working alongside us in the temple..."


translate English day5_hk_T_2f15c2f6:


    pl "You're not wrong, but I feel like that's a rather simplified way of stating things."


translate English day5_hk_T_feb3b54a:


    hk "Heheh... I can tell you're exhausted. Please feel free to take the day off tomorrow."


translate English day5_hk_T_2fcf73f5:


    pl "Huh? That kind of thing is allowed?"


translate English day5_hk_T_13a1196e:


    hk "Yes, of course it is. {w}Don't forget that your body is on loan from God himself. You must treat it with the utmost respect and care it deserves."


translate English day5_hk_T_cda2133f:


    pl "Right... I'll do that then."


translate English day5_hk_T_e728c36c:


    nar "I can't bring myself to face the forever smiling bishop without feeling awkward, at least for today."


translate English day5_hk_T_e9edffac:


    nar "Despite still being in the middle of a conversation with them, I can't shake the discomfort that's sprung to mind."


translate English day5_hk_T_50414fae:


    nar "I've managed to sorely underestimate her abilities, having mistakenly prided myself on being the only one aware of her inner workings and secrets."


translate English day5_hk_T_619e38ce:


    nar "And yet here we are, carrying on as if nothing's happened. So of course I'd find myself at a loss for words."


translate English day5_hk_T_3304927f:


    pl "I heard something about some kind of sermon in the afternoon?"


translate English day5_hk_T_0610f8ee:


    hk "Did the auxiliary bishop tell you that?"


translate English day5_hk_T_f4e1b60d:


    pl "He might have let it slip. But as the star of the show, I feel like I have a right to know."


translate English day5_hk_T_4bfda3b0:


    hk "True. You are a big deal and very important. {w}And I'm overjoyed, incredibly so."


translate English day5_hk_T_ec67739f:


    pl "What do you mean by that?"


translate English day5_hk_T_e2b412c2:


    hk "Brother, I've heard word that you have received the grace of God, given unto your very own body."


translate English day5_hk_T_f6553b26:


    hk "As one of the countless witnesses to that joyous miracle, I couldn't be happier."


translate English day5_hk_T_b63554e6:


    pl "Mm... I had a feeling you might say something like that."


translate English day5_hk_T_08510d8e:


    nar "A grace of God... {w}I'm one of a select few who knows for sure whether it actually exists or not."


translate English day5_hk_T_80da7192:


    nar "It's the \"grace\" part that I especially have trouble digesting. {w}What could I have possibly done to deserve being graced by a divine being like God?"


translate English day5_hk_T_2195d9f6:


    nar "At the very least, it should be given to someone far more worthy, such as a priest who's devoted his whole life to serving God. {w}Someone like this woman before me."


translate English day5_hk_T_dbc2e7e2:


    pl "And if I really have been graced, then it comes with the burden of knowing you must return the favor, right?"


translate English day5_hk_T_41795200:


    pl "And I don't have the faintest idea how to pay something like this back."


translate English day5_hk_T_226b9abf:


    hk "The debt of gratitude is an eternal back and forth."


translate English day5_hk_T_1278adb5:


    hk "The truth is I owe our father who art in heaven for the countless blessings he has bestowed upon me throughout my life, which continues with no apparent end in sight."


translate English day5_hk_T_2cd152ab:


    hk "Do not forget to respect and honor our Holy Father, Brother [na]. {w}Everything you have in life is thanks to the faith you harbor for him."


translate English day5_hk_T_514c6cbc:


    pl "If he's given me everything, then how exactly do I repay him?"


translate English day5_hk_T_7812bed0:


    hk "Ensure that every action carried out is done in respect to Him. {w}Working alongside your fellow brothers and sisters, eating your daily meals, everything..."


translate English day5_hk_T_131c89d9:


    pl "But those things only affect ourselves, right?"


translate English day5_hk_T_b9e211e5:


    hk "The lord has graced us with his blessings. {w}And so in order to show our gratitude, we must do what we can on an individual basis. We must help others and live virtuously."


translate English day5_hk_T_402af5ad:


    hk "Our father who art in heaven says to honor him. {w}And if honor is synonymous to faith, then God cherishes those whose belief in him is stronger than others."


translate English day5_hk_T_d997ca92:


    hk "Which is why I will continue to live piously and virtuously for our eternal Father."


translate English day5_hk_T_aa30a44d:


    pl "You know, up until now, I always assumed you used the word 'Father' as another name for God..."


translate English day5_hk_T_2a26e8e4:


    pl "But sometimes when you use the word 'father,' I get the feeling you're referring to your actual parent. I always thought that was kind of bizarre..."


translate English day5_hk_T_85d90cda:


    hk "Of course. He is the one who blessed me with the gift of life, after all."


translate English day5_hk_T_a0e1edb5:


    hk "My revered father is the one who commanded me to stand on my own two feet, and who gave me the power to do so--"


translate English day5_hk_T_68f2802a:


    hk "He imparted to me the wisdom to see the world with my own two eyes--who taught me the truth so that my tongue could move of its own volition."


translate English day5_hk_T_0ae3a590:


    hk "His merciful grace doesn't end with me, either. It extends to and encompasses every single person living and working within this temple."


translate English day5_hk_T_423d6e31:


    hk "And that person is my father, the cardinal of this temple."


translate English day5_hk_T_244a1b15:


    nar "I have occasionally heard that her father is the cardinal."


translate English day5_hk_T_3a550a34:


    nar "The cardinal of Saint Sheol, who created the scapegoat of a department, the Cleanup Department, for the benefit of the capital and the safety of the temple."


translate English day5_hk_T_e257e519:


    nar "Who let a poor, inexperienced priest die in their care and let his own daughter take the fall for it."


translate English day5_hk_T_ad2e56e8:


    hk "The thing about the cardinal is that he is a truly spectacular being."


translate English day5_hk_T_4ab92f48:


    hk "He took me in when I was but a young and inexperienced child and raised me as one of his own."


translate English day5_hk_T_8085ed2a:


    hk "I was naturally born faithless, and yet...he turned me into a believer."


translate English day5_hk_T_a9f096fc:


    hk "I was born powerless and yet he taught me how to be self-sufficient."


translate English day5_hk_T_c6aabcf8:


    hk "I am reminded of my father's mercy and compassion every hour, every second, and every minute I work here in the temple. {w}He means everything to me."


translate English day5_hk_T_d52d0d6f:


    hk "He is my pride, my emotions, my love!"


translate English day5_hk_T_8468ab00:


    nar "A golden fire shines forth from within her pale face. {w}I struggle to keep my mouth shut, not wanting to say something I'll regret later."


translate English day5_hk_T_10415fe6:


    nar "I don't nod or make any noise whatsoever. {w}I've never experienced anything like this before."


translate English day5_hk_T_8d1ad680:


    nar "I've grown up thinking the only way to get on an adult's good side is to respond positively to everything they say, even if you don't agree."


translate English day5_hk_T_ac503f44:


    nar "But I've grown so tired of everything coming out of her mouth that I simply don't want to listen to another word."


translate English day5_hk_T_bc18829a:


    nar "And yet her expression of rapture is stronger than ever. {w}It's like she's forgotten all about me, completely submerged in her own private rapture."


translate English day5_hk_T_e628541b:


    pl "If he really taught you about freedom and truth, then why can't you speak even one or two words about your own personal desires?"


translate English day5_hk_T_5fcb7d29:


    hk "The first thing I want is peace. {w}Then love. And finally, God's grace."


translate English day5_hk_T_d3c04e2c:


    pl "Not this again... Well, it doesn't sound like there's anything I can do. {w}Honestly, I wish you'd been graced by God instead of me."


translate English day5_hk_T_be9dbb8e:


    hk "That's absurd. God has chosen you, Brother...!"


translate English day5_hk_T_5b8b066b:


    pl "And I chose you, remember?"


translate English day5_hk_T_5744c7a3:


    hk "I do... and for that I am joyous beyond all words‚ô™ {w}I thank God Almighty for the spectacular choice you've made..."


translate English day5_hk_T_cde37970:


    pl "You should be thanking me for that, not God... {w}Though I have no idea how exactly this works."


translate English day5_hk_T_83aef1aa:


    hk "It is said that if you eat an eye, you will be granted the power of sight, and if you devour a heart, the power of life itself."


translate English day5_hk_T_6668e856:


    hk "I wonder... If I were to consume your arm, would the grace you received be bestowed upon myself as well?"


translate English day5_hk_T_6a6a1b9d:


    pl "Ha ha ha! I'd like to see you try. {w}Seriously."


translate English day5_hk_T_d576710d:


    nar "I'm starting to get annoyed. {w}A part of me is grateful it's so dark here so she can't see the expression on my face."


translate English day5_hk_T_96553d2f:


    nar "She utters words like \"freedom\" and \"love\" to describe the feelings she holds for her father."


translate English day5_hk_T_2a137c7a:


    nar "She's almost like a puppet parroting back emotions that were forced into her brain. {w}In which case, do I really need her?"


translate English day5_hk_T_b7f54ba2:


    nar "Unpleasant and uncomfortable feelings being bubbling up inside me, one after another. {w}Almost as if in direct response to how little I care about her."


translate English day5_hk_T_20d4d5bb:


    pl "I get the feeling that you tend to use 'faith' and 'trust' in the religious sense. {w}You seem to be equating a man to that of God."


translate English day5_hk_T_41eb747a:


    hk "I am? {w}Is that truly how you see things?"


translate English day5_hk_T_14d055f1:


    hk "While it's true that faith springs naturally from the heart of a believer, I am well aware that my father and our Eternal Father are not one and the same."


translate English day5_hk_T_a8f5555b:


    hk "I simply believe in God as one of his faithful followers might."


translate English day5_hk_T_f651af3a:


    pl "In that case, I might need to say a couple Hail Mary's."


translate English day5_hk_T_88d78a5f:


    pl "Because I'm still not sure of my own faith. And that, in itself, is a sin, am I right?"


translate English day5_hk_T_2f06c915:


    hk "Ignorance is not a sin. {w}It is the willful refusal to teach what you know that is a sin, Brother."


translate English day5_hk_T_e7028d4e:


    hk "If there is something you don't understand, then it is my duty to enlighten you."


translate English day5_hk_T_43c1ac0c:


    nar "With her eyes tightly closed, she places her thumbs, her index fingers, and then her middle fingers together."


translate English day5_hk_T_b999c84d:


    nar "She then moves her hands, still pressed together, just above where her heart would be, drawing a line across her chest. {w}The gesture is somehow familiar to me."


translate English day5_hk_T_370a1d21:


    pl "What did you just do?"


translate English day5_hk_T_6bc5e62f:


    hk "I drew the sign of the cross. It's a ritual that marks the beginning and end of the liturgy."


translate English day5_hk_T_cc000e5e:


    hk "Brother [na]? It seems like someone's been neglecting their studies."


translate English day5_hk_T_7cda764f:


    pl "You're right, but you should be used to it by now. {w}So, if you would be so kind as to enlighten this ignorant fool, Your Excellency."


translate English day5_hk_T_44919c9c:


    hk "That's pretty mean, considering how much effort I put into my lectures every morning!"


translate English day5_hk_T_90392300:


    hk "*sigh*... Alright, alright, listen carefully... {w}The fingers we place together symbolize the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit."


translate English day5_hk_T_6ce95199:


    hk "Each place we touch on the body is symbolic as well, making the order important or else you change the meaning."


translate English day5_hk_T_19a2870c:


    hk "Once done, we place both palms together and bow."


translate English day5_hk_T_7dd9ef9a:


    pl "I see... Can I try doing it on my own?"


translate English day5_hk_T_4a07dbb4:


    hk "I'm sorry, but no. There are certain rules we must abide by that differ per continent..."


translate English day5_hk_T_fa5b6114:


    hk "Though for us here in the Northern Continent... the meaning behind the gesture is flexible, in a matter of speaking. {w}We're not as strict..."


translate English day5_hk_T_1e97b6d7:


    pl "Then pray for me."


translate English day5_hk_T_cb19d50a:


    nar "Letting my emotions get the best of me, I find myself blurting out that childish saying. {w}The space between us momentarily sinks into breathless silence..."


translate English day5_hk_T_60c76010:


    nar "Which the bishop almost immediately breaks, smiling meaningfully at me as she clasps her hands together with her usual chaotic movements."


translate English day5_hk_T_c06b432c:


    nar "Her candle sits almost precariously close, the flame wavering dangerously with even the slightest movement."


translate English day5_hk_T_a5ec8b53:


    nar "I watch her with bated breathe as she moves her hands from her forehead to her left shoulder, then left shoulder to chest, then chest to stomach."


translate English day5_hk_T_663e1caa:


    hk "I'm sure you must be wondering what this means."


translate English day5_hk_T_fcace51b:


    nar "With all five of her fingers fully outstretched, she places one palm against the other."


translate English day5_hk_T_167156ee:


    nar "I look up once again into her face, studying her expression, but instead of looking back, she uses that same gesture on me, {w}this time moving from my forehead to my left shoulder, and then left shoulder to chest."


translate English day5_hk_T_9be1487f:


    hk "It has been decided that the nobleman, descended from heaven, will stay in the underworld as one of our priests."


translate English day5_hk_T_919d77b4:


    hk "And then, shall return."


translate English day5_hk_T_41067fbe:


    nar "She ends the sign on my stomach. {w}The corners of my mouth lift reflexively, but my throat is quickly getting dry due to being stuck here in this putrid place for too long."


translate English day5_hk_T_c037b0b9:


    nar "She watches me without even a hint of ridicule on her face, despite how bizarre the expression on my face must look in that moment."


translate English day5_hk_T_df2cc740:


    pl "Don't bullshit me... God doesn't come up in that story even once, and there's no meaning behind the sign you just drew."


translate English day5_hk_T_aa942720:


    hk "You're not incorrect, Brother. What you say is true."


translate English day5_hk_T_99808253:


    hk "But for those of us who believe in their very souls, the gesture is far from meaningless bullshit."


translate English day5_hk_T_4ef1138d:


    pl "Where I come from, we have a word known as 'repentance.' {w}We must repent for the sins we've committed over multiple reincarnated lifetimes."


translate English day5_hk_T_9772da62:


    pl "I'm not entirely sure if 'repentance' and 'contrition' are the same... {w}but the adults often referred to it as the purification of karma."


translate English day5_hk_T_9f5b1751:


    hk "It's got a beautiful ring to it, doesn't it? Does that same word exist elsewhere?"


translate English day5_hk_T_59d67b29:


    pl "Yes. We walk through the morning mist, clapping our hands twice and shouting, 'Repent! Repent!'"


translate English day5_hk_T_365ac155:


    pl "I guess that means something, too."


translate English day5_hk_T_978e8f82:


    hk "With your loud voices and resonant sounds, it seems as if you are trying to reach something that is a far, far away."


translate English day5_hk_T_aaf86dfb:


    pl "Whether the meaning got through or not, it was enough to startle me awake from deep sleep."


translate English day5_hk_T_d6551e4e:


    hk "Wow! It sounds like the act of penance awakened your very spirit, Brother [na]."


translate English day5_hk_T_26a1c525:


    pl "I don't think it went that deep... {w}Though I guess that's a fair point to make."


translate English day5_hk_T_4e9d5db4:


    pl "It was never just one or two people, though. Every single adult in the village would participate in this creepy ritual, as if on some kind of sin patrol."


translate English day5_hk_T_e5c559dc:


    hk "Sins pass from one to another, you know. {w}But blessings do the same."


translate English day5_hk_T_0d5a8ffd:


    nar "The air that fills this place is quite possibly the strangest substance I've ever inhaled."


translate English day5_hk_T_8520c53c:


    nar "The thick dust that carpets everything, the drippings from the candle as it melts, and the putrefied decomposition that clings to every tool... {w}I should be struggling to breathe, and yet surprisingly, I seem unaffected."


translate English day5_hk_T_0e304489:


    pl "Your Excellency..."


translate English day5_hk_T_f6c323e0:


    nar "I try to continue, but as soon as our eyes meet, all the words scatter from my mind."


translate English day5_hk_T_679c036b:


    nar "I worry I will lose an essential part of my being if I remain here for much longer."


translate English day5_hk_T_c16b3f43:


    nar "Her eyes are so mysterious that they seem almost otherworldly, and that smile of hers is enough to make my mind go blank."


translate English day5_hk_T_dc6c5ed3:


    pl "If you truly believe in me that strongly, then I want to offer you the blessing I received."


translate English day5_hk_T_72eea9a2:


    pl "If you can accept me as the Human I am now, then perhaps some of my karmic sins can be erased. {w}And if that in turn leads me toward the path of the believer,"


translate English day5_hk_T_23b4adf6:


    pl "then it will make me feel better than I do now."


translate English day5_hk_T_f444b1b6:


    nar "I sound insane. {w}I feel like I've fallen into some delusional trance, the words pouring from my mouth as if forced out against my will."


translate English day5_hk_T_aa5493a1:


    nar "But she just looks at me with her plain and simple face, ever smiling, as if she had expected this might happen."


translate English day5_hk_T_24c89343:


    hk "They share their bodies with us, like a manifestation of the sacrament. {w}Like carving the memories and emotions of our fellow Brothers and Sisters into our bodies."


translate English day5_hk_T_a826801f:


    pl "The sacrament..."


translate English day5_hk_T_5ecce0f0:


    hk "Yes... Although the Eucharist was always supposed to melt slowly in one's mouth, which is a problem, isn't it?"


translate English day5_hk_T_2cda6233:


    pl "You don't have to act so polite around me. I've already decided to pass my grace and belief onto you."


translate English day5_hk_T_165aa8ea:


    nar "Just like the man who blessed her with faith before. {w}Talking like this is only making my thirst worse."


translate English day5_hk_T_8f0cbcee:


    nar "Her softly smiling face appears soaked in blood thanks to the glow from the crimson candle."


translate English day5_hk_T_a26e5086:


    nar "She grips my shoulders tightly in her smooth, leather-clad hands. {w}I hold my breath as long as I can."


translate English day5_hk_T_d963b85d:


    nar "Expectation, relief, and fear surge through me at once."


translate English day5_hk_T_1b544d17:


    nar "I change my mind once I catch sight of those translucent vermilion veins, her sharp teeth, and the sticky drool that dribbles out between them."


translate English day5_hk_T_9fb66811:


    nar "I would drown in these feelings of revulsion forever if I could."


translate English day5_hk_T_b3211ba0:


    nar "As my vision goes black, I hear the soft sound of feathers in my head."


translate English day5_hk_T_5c4cc346:


    nar "Surprised, my eyes snap open, although I still can't see anything. {w}I guess a gust of wind blew out the candle."


translate English day5_hk_T_2b52a409:


    nar "I force myself to inhale and then exhale, and before long, the candle's flame returns to life. {w}I see Haku, standing there with a match in one hand, still smiling."


translate English day5_hk_T_2f73fff5:


    hk "Even when the sun is out, this warehouse is perpetually shrouded in darkness."


translate English day5_hk_T_01032aa8:


    hk "My father was always afraid of the machinery rusting, so he made sure to fill in any gaps to keep the light out."


translate English day5_hk_T_bc4ddb47:


    hk "The Cleanup Department is another space where light cannot penetrate. {w}It's pretty hard to enjoy being in a space as dimly lit as this one, hm?"


translate English day5_hk_T_90ebe612:


    nar "With candle in hand, she walks slowly over to the warehouse door, which she opens."


translate English day5_hk_T_8b545f0f:


    nar "Both her and the candle flame wobble to and fro. {w}Outside I spot a black bird, the name of which I do not know."


translate English day5_hk_T_ba687a75:


    hk "Thank you for the meal."


translate English day5_hk_T_f740c78f:


    nar "Before stepping outside, she turns and speaks to me. {w}She is illuminated in a bright white glow, not red."


translate English day5_hk_T_01402bbf:


    nar "I find myself stunned as I stand all alone in the warehouse, the door wide open. {w}I'd only been inside for a short time, and yet for some reason, I can't remember anything."


translate English day5_hk_T_421f4ca4:


    nar "Only her words remained in my mind, almost as if she had bewitched me in some way."


translate English day5_hk_T_d8774ef8:


    nar "This is the underworld. {w}Where only those who have forgotten the passage of time in death dwell."


translate English day5_hk_T_a73cd515:


    nar "Some do occasionally end up in heaven or in hell, but no one ever knows where they truly are at any given moment."


translate English day5_hk_T_a29eae29:


    nar "My stomach grumbles."


translate English day5_gr_T_1c71f15c:


    br "\n Dr. Grette often urged me to keep a journal of sorts. {w}I'd constantly ask why, though the answer she gave back was always the same.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_gr_T_63f8c85f:


    extend "\nAnd so I sit my utterly exhausted body down in my hard chair before going to sleep. {w}I light a candle in order to help me see better,{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_gr_T_3c412d56:


    extend "\nbut to my surprise, I wasn't able to write even a single word before the flame went out. {w}Dr. Grette always reassured me it didn't matter how boring it might sound,{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_gr_T_ee61d406:


    extend "\nbut stressed how the most important part was simply to reflect back on your day and write about how you felt. {w}And yet I still couldn't bring myself to document something so utterly mundane."


translate English day5_gr_T_99352cc5:



    nvl clear
    br "\nI'd always return the blank journal to the doctor and she'd always accept it knowing full well there was nothing inside, leaving a short note for me in the bottom corner of a page.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_gr_T_4a43aef4:


    extend "\nShe leaves me a short, silly letter every day, as if somehow knowing what it was I had wanted to write.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_gr_T_5ae5854a:


    extend "\nI continue to light a candle every night, staring at what she's left for me at the bottom of that blank piece of paper."


translate English day5_gr_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_gr_T_0cb14e12:


    nar "I might have come a little too early, as the infirmary remains dark."


translate English day5_gr_T_27e0606b:


    nar "Normally, light spills out through the open door or through the window, accompanied by the sweet smell of candy."


translate English day5_gr_T_6fefe830:


    nar "The dark and empty corridor feels unfamiliar."


translate English day5_gr_T_721eb547:


    nar "I should have just gone back, but I stand there a moment longer, staring at the closed door."


translate English day5_gr_T_2573b576:


    nar "I'm not sure how it got in, but a small, moth-like creature flits around just in front of me."


translate English day5_gr_T_2d9677fd:


    nar "The moth, unable to support itself, suddenly slams into the wall, crushing its body against the unyielding surface."


translate English day5_gr_T_c116f514:


    nar "And yet, it continues flapping its wings, as if unaware of the wall in front of it, continually ramming itself against this dark obstacle."


translate English day5_gr_T_cc24f5f1:


    nar "Watching it makes me feel uncomfortable for reasons I don't understand."


translate English day5_gr_T_74a7dc96:


    pl "!!!"


translate English day5_gr_T_7a58e378:


    nar "I hear the sound of footsteps coming down the silent corridor. {w}The light echo of slippers, something you never hear as part of the Disposal Team."


translate English day5_gr_T_bbb38b14:


    nar "There are only a few folks here in the temple who could make those footsteps."


translate English day5_gr_T_54f740c2:


    gr "Now what do we have here?"


translate English day5_gr_T_35dc0473:


    pl "Doctor!"


translate English day5_gr_T_834bb942:


    nar "My joy over the sudden appearance of the exact woman I'd been waiting for immediately vanishes when I notice the man standing idly by her side, his movements and appearance awkward and clumsy."


translate English day5_gr_T_eae01232:


    nar "It's him. {w}The guy I saw earlier in the temple hospital. The Bishop of the Health Department."


translate English day5_gr_T_44e4b54b:


    gr "Were you waiting for me, [na2]? {w}I'm sorry for running late. What can I do for you?"


translate English day5_gr_T_2c109654:


    pl "It's okay, really. I honestly just arrived, so I hadn't been waiting for very long. {w}What are you...?"


translate English day5_gr_T_5e1a02c2:


    gr "Whew... {w}We actually just finished up work. I was about to take a much needed break."


translate English day5_gr_T_23443b54:


    gr "Do you want to come inside and have a cup of tea or something?"


translate English day5_gr_T_5e13511a:


    nar "Perhaps noticing what's wrong, Dr. Grette swings open the door and ushers me inside more urgently than usual."


translate English day5_gr_T_bcd4bd12:


    nar "It's not that I want to inconvenience Gregor or even that I don't want to see him,"


translate English day5_gr_T_9e0c6d12:


    nar "but more like I can't bring myself to look at him after what happened earlier at the hospital."


translate English day5_gr_T_1a01cfcb:


    nar "I wish he'd either yell at me or at least say hello. His silence is frustratingly annoying."


translate English day5_gr_T_310727c7:


    gr "I'm sorry, [na2]. Is black tea okay?"


translate English day5_gr_T_34ca1df7:


    pl "Oh, yeah. Of course. I generally don't mind tea."


translate English day5_gr_T_d0d57ca1:


    nar "I blurt out that fairly ambiguous answer, but I've honestly never drank it in my life. {w}With a gentle smile, she retreats into a back room before bringing out what she needs to brew a pot."


translate English day5_gr_T_5dec9fc8:


    nar "The white tea cups have small flowers painted on them, just like the ones I always see."


translate English day5_gr_T_13b5b94e:


    nar "My thoughts vanish as I watch her pour the boiling hot water. {w}She holds the pot gingerly in both hands, steam drifting up into the air."


translate English day5_gr_T_f8e9bc0b:


    nar "The tea cup was filled with white steam even before it was filled with hot water, as if it had been preheated. {w}The pitch-black tea leaves float along the top, dying the water a deep red."


translate English day5_gr_T_67fde8a8:


    nar "Her hand, warming up the tea cakes. The same hand, pouring our tea into a set of cute cups. {w}The hand that so skillfully makes one cup after another, with that familiar silver band shining on one finger."


translate English day5_gr_T_931206ad:


    nar "I'd never noticed it before, but now that I have, it sparkles underneath the light, as if proud of its existence."


translate English day5_gr_T_0e48d70e:


    gr "Okay, all done."


translate English day5_gr_T_2ee61b39:


    nar "Still remaining silent, the man reaches forward to pick up one of the cups. {w}I'm so engrossed in his presence that I completely forget to thank her as I pick up my own cup."


translate English day5_gr_T_cf658e34:


    nar "My freezing hands are instantly warmed by the hot tea cup."


translate English day5_gr_T_db6d0a23:


    nar "The peculiar aroma of tea leaves that passes over the palette to be exhaled through the nose. The bitterness that lingers after the taste of clean water has passed..."


translate English day5_gr_T_d279bb6b:


    nar "My mind can't make sense of it. It tastes as if someone infused water with perfume."


translate English day5_gr_T_965aae89:


    gg "You're getting better and better at making tea."


translate English day5_gr_T_fd0e6078:


    pl "He's right. This is really tasty."


translate English day5_gr_T_a6cd42e3:


    nar "I follow up his sudden compliment with one of my own."


translate English day5_gr_T_97e72548:


    nar "It was only a simple word of praise, and yet as she stands here, plate in hand, her face immediately brightens, glowing like the morning sun."


translate English day5_gr_T_316fcf7f:


    nar "The sight of that leaves me feeling oddly guilty."


translate English day5_gr_T_3de4506b:


    gr "I know, right? I got this as a gift recently, so I absolutely had to share it with you."


translate English day5_gr_T_9e0ac2e4:


    pl "Mm... I feel like I'm intruding on your private tea party here. I'll get out of your hair as soon as I finish."


translate English day5_gr_T_539c2cc9:


    gr "What are you babbling about?! I made this tea for you, too, [na2]. {w}Don't feel like you need to rush off. Feel free to stay as long as you'd like."


translate English day5_gr_T_f218222d:


    pl "But..."


translate English day5_gr_T_539d488b:


    gr "I had a chat with Lavi on the way over and she gave this to me."


translate English day5_gr_T_312ceffe:


    gr "I had a cup myself already, and the aroma is truly splendid. I was delightfully surprised when I took my first sip."


translate English day5_gr_T_5fe5cba4:


    pl "You got this from Lavi, huh?"


translate English day5_gr_T_9e0c5e48:


    gr "Oh! You've met her before, [na2]?"


translate English day5_gr_T_d5e105e2:


    gr "She's a very smart and capable girl, which is why she's Evelynn's favorite."


translate English day5_gr_T_984eaa98:


    pl "Though I rarely get to see her. Maybe it's a specialty among auxiliary bishops?"


translate English day5_gr_T_0d36f51d:


    nar "Is she referring to the habit of making tea? Well, it seems like something the Academics Department would do, considering their penchant for drinking pungent beverages."


translate English day5_gr_T_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day5_gr_T_51567231:


    pl "Does that mean you became the auxiliary bishop here in the Health Department because you're the bishop's favorite?"


translate English day5_gr_T_7f2381c4:


    gr "Pardon me?"


translate English day5_gr_T_2ea6ca32:


    gg "The appointment of an auxiliary bishop is not dictated by one's personal preferences."


translate English day5_gr_T_440429cb:


    gg "The reason why Grette holds the position she does is due to her competence and qualifications."


translate English day5_gr_T_d61c2685:


    gr "H-Having the two of you gang up on me like this is really embarrassing...!"


translate English day5_gr_T_a5521281:


    pl "I do get the feeling the Health Department wouldn't be able to function without Dr. Grette's help."


translate English day5_gr_T_437577db:


    gr "Rrgh... Oh, no! I can't believe myself! We can't have a proper tea party without sweets. {w}Hang on... I'll go get some right away!"


translate English day5_gr_T_fb18e5a4:


    nar "With her cheeks colored deep crimson, she scurries off into the kitchen located at the back of the infirmary."


translate English day5_gr_T_e555e1e0:


    nar "I've never seen her act so flustered before. {w}Either she's extraordinarily bad at accepting praise, or..."


translate English day5_gr_T_eb854be6:


    gg "..."


translate English day5_gr_T_15f74d69:


    nar "The bishop continues sipping his tea, as if used to this sort of behavior from her."


translate English day5_gr_T_351eceab:


    nar "Suddenly, the two of us are alone together. I hate this kind of social awkwardness..."


translate English day5_gr_T_032f79ce:


    gg "Have you gotten used to the job yet?"


translate English day5_gr_T_7631af35:


    pl "Huh?"


translate English day5_gr_T_8d15e99f:


    nar "I can't believe my ears at first. {w}I didn't think he would be the first to break the silence. I guess he couldn't stand the awkwardness either."


translate English day5_gr_T_bcdaf3cd:


    pl "Uh, well, actually... {w}Things haven't necessarily gotten easier, but at least it's gotten less bad as the days go by."


translate English day5_gr_T_06b4068c:


    pl "I'm almost done working in the Disposal... {w}er, in the Clean-Up Department. Honestly, I'm more worried about you after what happened."


translate English day5_gr_T_51bb8f90:


    gg "Right, you mentioned something about being transferred to the Magic Department."


translate English day5_gr_T_3f16b3a1:


    pl "Yep. Geez, word seem to get around here. I'm still lacking in experience and knowledge, though..."


translate English day5_gr_T_62258a6d:


    gg "Of course. I initially started working here at the temple around the same ago as you. I remember how difficult everything was at first."


translate English day5_gr_T_0629aa6c:


    gg "Listen to the older priests and your supervisors."


translate English day5_gr_T_003198f4:


    pl "Supervisors? You mean like Bishop Haku? {w}Do you know the bishop of my department well?"


translate English day5_gr_T_dfdffefb:


    gg "Well enough."


translate English day5_gr_T_17d669bd:


    pl "Wow, I had no idea... {w}Do you tend to meet with the other bishops often since you hold similar positions? Kind of like with Bishop Evelynn?"


translate English day5_gr_T_38594ddc:


    gg "Didn't Grette tell you?"


translate English day5_gr_T_60f84352:


    pl "The doctor?"


translate English day5_gr_T_54031aed:


    gg "The three of us--myself, Grette, and Evelynn Violeta--all attended the same academy."


translate English day5_gr_T_e535b54f:


    pl "This is the first I'm hearing of it... Then the three of you have been friends for a long time, huh?"


translate English day5_gr_T_a77fb6e3:


    gg "Is that also unexpected?"


translate English day5_gr_T_27ccd670:


    pl "Well... Kind of."


translate English day5_gr_T_ceb48658:


    nar "A long-lasting bond between three friends who attended the same academy and all ended up in same place... {w}The puzzle pieces are finally starting to fit together in my head."


translate English day5_gr_T_c097e871:


    pl "If I may... Do you know about the ring Dr. Grette wears on her left hand?"


translate English day5_gr_T_094900e0:


    gg "Of course I do."


translate English day5_gr_T_6aa932be:


    pl "I was just curious... when did she get that?"


translate English day5_gr_T_fde31cf5:


    gg "A long time ago. A little under ten years back, I believe."


translate English day5_gr_T_303a2791:


    pl "I thought dating within the temple was forbidden though...right?"


translate English day5_gr_T_d27b85b1:


    nar "I hesitantly ask and the bishop sighs in response."


translate English day5_gr_T_92f00d8d:


    gg "I was under the same impression, but... Well, she can be frustratingly obstinate at times. {w}It happened a long time ago. Truly, no one can stop her from doing what she wants."


translate English day5_gr_T_0e0624c3:


    nar "Hearing his sharp tone of voice coupled with the thinly veiled distaste over past memories that crosses his face, I become sure of something."


translate English day5_gr_T_fdfe62a2:


    nar "This is the man who made Dr. Grette into the woman she is today."


translate English day5_gr_T_eb91839c:


    pl "So she's kept this relationship a secret for ten years?"


translate English day5_gr_T_dad16d7f:


    gg "Those who know, know. {w}The real question is why our behavior is silently tolerated instead of called out..."


translate English day5_gr_T_871b4f99:


    pl "Are you sure you should be telling me this?"


translate English day5_gr_T_67cf41d0:


    gg "You're clearly aware of what's going on anyway, right? {w}Besides, it clearly means a lot to her."


translate English day5_gr_T_288450f8:


    pl "Th-That may be true, but I'm sure you don't agree with it..."


translate English day5_gr_T_bcf0e59d:


    gg "You want to know what I think? {w}One of her talents is that all the youngsters here in the temple adore her. So I don't see a problem with it."


translate English day5_gr_T_2a28b34c:


    pl "Dr. Grette once told me... {w}The reason she's been able to stay here in the temple as long as she has is because of you."


translate English day5_gr_T_07a0dac0:


    gg "...She really said that?"


translate English day5_gr_T_13e7a844:


    pl "Do you really think I'd be able to influence anyone else's opinions or feelings around here?"


translate English day5_gr_T_a2ebf235:


    pl "Like Dr. Grette said, any words of wisdom to share with me?"


translate English day5_gr_T_1fc26886:


    gg "You're clearly after something."


translate English day5_gr_T_a9927e30:


    pl "That's not true... I'm not striving to be the best at anything, similar to how you feel. I just want to be able to put the people around me at ease."


translate English day5_gr_T_610c003e:


    gg "In that case, I'll tell you how I do it."


translate English day5_gr_T_6c0c3f17:


    pl "Really?"


translate English day5_gr_T_51e22eab:


    gg "First of all, make sure you don't work that injured arm of yours more than necessary. {w}And try not to get hurt again."


translate English day5_gr_T_01371518:


    gg "Finally, talk to us. Don't keep your worries bottled up inside. {w}That's all there is."


translate English day5_gr_T_e4c3fc8f:


    pl "Seriously? That seems more like personal advice instead of how I can help the people around me."


translate English day5_gr_T_077342ea:


    gg "Why is it that when we think about helping others, we remove ourselves from the equation?"


translate English day5_gr_T_f2887ae2:


    pl "Well..."


translate English day5_gr_T_0964c56f:


    gg "Misfortune and unhappiness ultimately affects all of us."


translate English day5_gr_T_99e6b7de:


    gg "If, while working hard for the sake of others, you fall ill, then we cannot complete the job we were tasked with, correct?"


translate English day5_gr_T_f27e7e7d:


    pl "Huh. You've always struck me as standoffish. I had no idea you were such a preacher at heart."


translate English day5_gr_T_0f4c9caa:


    gg "Everything I say is for your own good. Don't dismiss my words as a mere lecture on your actions."


translate English day5_gr_T_e9dca278:


    nar "*sigh*... This prime example of a doddering old fool needs to get to the point already..."


translate English day5_gr_T_02603fcd:


    gg "I try to provide the utmost care to every patient placed in my custody. {w}And right now, you are one of my patients."


translate English day5_gr_T_069f0518:


    pl "I'm not really interested in being treated like a patient."


translate English day5_gr_T_8c0a916a:


    gg "Truly? Well, that much is obvious. {w}Is there something you'd like instead?"


translate English day5_gr_T_c7a91648:


    pl "Something I want..."


translate English day5_gr_T_5b06e7fc:


    gr "Sorry for making you two wait!"


translate English day5_gr_T_77b17675:


    nar "Our conversation comes to an abrupt end as soon as Dr. Grette scurries back in. {w}She's holding a plate that's covered in all manner of baked goods, including several rolled-up pastries."


translate English day5_gr_T_afca5e4c:


    gr "Are scones okay?"


translate English day5_gr_T_4a3ede73:


    pl "Those are scones? They don't look like any scone I've seen before."


translate English day5_gr_T_20ffd2b1:


    gr "Hehehe! Scones are fascinating pastries that can be baked into any shape one fancies."


translate English day5_gr_T_ff7b5edf:


    gr "I know you're not a big fan of chocolate, [na2], so I made some with raisins."


translate English day5_gr_T_42c707a3:


    pl "Wow, you noticed that about me?"


translate English day5_gr_T_8ef61b75:


    gr "I know quite a bit about you, [na2]. I am a doctor, after all!"


translate English day5_gr_T_c437dacf:


    pl "Well, this is kind of embarrassing... Everything you make is delicious, though, so I'll happily eat anything you give me."


translate English day5_gr_T_0605392e:


    nar "She takes her rightful place next to the bishop, facing me."


translate English day5_gr_T_4e89e131:


    gr "What did you say to this young fellow while I was gone?"


translate English day5_gr_T_00f5686e:


    gg "Nothing nearly as good as what you're about to tell him."


translate English day5_gr_T_19a3ff81:


    gr "And what's that supposed to mean? {w}It's my duty as a counselor to protect the right to privacy granted to everyone who comes to me for help, you know."


translate English day5_gr_T_5435da5c:


    pl "Sorry, doc, but you already said that."


translate English day5_gr_T_1a8d90a6:


    gr "What?!"


translate English day5_gr_T_e99d10ba:


    gr "I didn't do any such thing! You big jerk!"


translate English day5_gr_T_25ce5c93:


    gg "Big talk for someone who so shamelessly walks around with a ring on her finger."


translate English day5_gr_T_a3c86827:


    pl "Ha! Not like that's a big deal or anything! Don't worry about it! You're not doing anything wrong!"


translate English day5_gr_T_49fc5508:


    nar "That's right, she ISN'T doing anything wrong. She has her own life and I have no reason to get involved in her business."


translate English day5_gr_T_b4cfa6f6:


    nar "An awkwardness descends on us born from simple shock."


translate English day5_gr_T_409ba43f:


    nar "Needless to say, the discomfort is almost palpable..."


translate English day5_gr_T_669bb0bf:


    nar "..."


translate English day5_gr_T_15dbe8f6:


    gr "Ngh... Do whatever you want. See if I care."


translate English day5_gr_T_b96035ad:


    pl "I think it's nice to have a sense of family."


translate English day5_gr_T_ac7d2a13:


    gr "I'm not sure if two people constitute a family... though there's not much that can be done about that."


translate English day5_gr_T_0e084dcd:


    gr "Speaking of family, [na2], I don't think I ever asked about yours though I've heard quite a bit about your hometown already."


translate English day5_gr_T_815e042a:


    gr "What's your father and mother like?"


translate English day5_gr_T_a8dd13ea:


    pl "My family?"


translate English day5_gr_T_ad4358b4:


    nar "I can talk endlessly about my siblings, but my memories regarding my own parents are hazy at best."


translate English day5_gr_T_430ae25f:


    nar "In a village like mine where everyone is related, the idea of \"parents\" doesn't really exist the way it does here."


translate English day5_gr_T_72447ae9:


    pl "I don't have a mother."


translate English day5_gr_T_7e092507:


    gr "Uh..."


translate English day5_gr_T_dcc941cc:


    nar "A chill of loneliness sweeps through the room. {w}Well, aside from Greg, who can never seem to read the room."


translate English day5_gr_T_a5f97f03:


    nar "The sorrow in Dr. Grette's eyes speaks volumes of how brave she thinks I am for saying what I did."


translate English day5_gr_T_523f8b27:


    pl "Don't look at me like that! I honestly didn't mean to bring the mood down or anything."


translate English day5_gr_T_138d1089:


    pl "The place I grew up in was pretty unique in that we were all siblings."


translate English day5_gr_T_6585ae59:


    pl "The adults raised the lot of us as group, treating us as if we were their own flesh and blood."


translate English day5_gr_T_c1b050a1:


    pl "Though, to be fair, I was the only boy my age that didn't die of sickness, leaving me to grow up basically alone."


translate English day5_gr_T_7133dabb:


    pl "But then I ended up leaving my hometown behind and coming here to the capital."


translate English day5_gr_T_0165b07d:


    pl "Anyways, it's not like I never saw the face of the woman who gave birth to me. She just never felt like my mother."


translate English day5_gr_T_48bf838d:


    pl "I don't think anyone did. {w}Since all the adults acted as my parents, it's impossible for me to pick out one or two people who I felt any special way about."


translate English day5_gr_T_01e67268:


    pl "I accepted our way of life because that's all I knew, but after arriving in the capital and hearing about the more traditional family structure here,"


translate English day5_gr_T_915389db:


    pl "I'm not even really sure what the word 'parent' means anymore."


translate English day5_gr_T_4d873d84:


    nar "I'd only planned on saying a few words on the matter, but it's almost like I can't stop talking."


translate English day5_gr_T_b3a07325:


    nar "I'm sure it's partly due to the laid-back atmosphere in the room. {w}Or perhaps it's partly born of my desire to fill the awkward silence."


translate English day5_gr_T_6a55480d:


    gr "Can you hang on for a moment, [na2]?"


translate English day5_gr_T_ad82f27c:


    nar "Dr. Grette, who'd been silently watching me during my monologue, suddenly jumps to her feet and heads to her desk, covered in piles of paperwork."


translate English day5_gr_T_6988525a:


    nar "She quickly returns carrying a rather thin photo album and a curious looking camera."


translate English day5_gr_T_b72a694d:


    gr "This is called a Polaroid camera."


translate English day5_gr_T_42522300:


    gr "It's a pretty convenient camera that instantly develops whatever photo you take."


translate English day5_gr_T_33ee21a2:


    pl "Wow, I never saw anything like it. So this is how you take photos, huh?"


translate English day5_gr_T_3e81ea09:


    gr "Heh heh heh! I love taking photos, and every year, I put together a photo album, just like this one."


translate English day5_gr_T_ac48eeee:


    gr "Do you want to try holding it?"


translate English day5_gr_T_2c5230d7:


    pl "Huh? Me?"


translate English day5_gr_T_fa4a3b64:


    gr "Don't be shy!"


translate English day5_gr_T_8e6a398e:


    nar "The camera ends up being a lot lighter than it looks. {w}Though it seems pretty difficult to work and fairly old as well."


translate English day5_gr_T_ed8081a4:


    nar "I'm sure it's something that holds a considerable number of memories."


translate English day5_gr_T_179aa27d:


    nar "Although unsure how to hold it at first, I quickly bring the camera to my face, peering through the round lens."


translate English day5_gr_T_8f80d277:


    gg "That's not actually the shutter. It's a little lower."


translate English day5_gr_T_6a0f806b:


    pl "L-Like this?"


translate English day5_gr_T_bc1b5bdd:


    gg "Exactly! Keep your eye on the lens."


translate English day5_gr_T_20ebd8f7:


    pl "Ooh."


translate English day5_gr_T_2eaa2f1a:


    gr "H-Hang on a minute! Are you trying to take a picture of me?"


translate English day5_gr_T_38a6a1b3:


    pl "I'm trying to get both of you in the photo!"


translate English day5_gr_T_bd3b25a1:


    gr "Hahaha... I'm so embarrassed! If you must, please try and get my good side!"


translate English day5_gr_T_03e9561b:


    pl "For someone as beautiful as you, all sides are your good side! {w}Right, Your Excellency?"


translate English day5_gr_T_2e865631:


    gg "I'm not sure about that. The lens is pretty old."


translate English day5_gr_T_c8452450:


    gr "Most people would have just agreed in this kind of situation. You really can't read the room, huh?"


translate English day5_gr_T_f00c359b:


    pl "Hahaha! It's okay."


translate English day5_gr_T_59bdd1af:


    nar "With a bright flash, the unfamiliar sound of the shutter snaps twice."


translate English day5_gr_T_42727c20:


    nar "The pitch-black sheet of paper the small machine spits out has an unexpectedly wet feeling to it, leaving me covered in unexplained goosebumps."


translate English day5_gr_T_90a721b3:


    pl "Why is it so black?"


translate English day5_gr_T_2bab7851:


    gr "Because you have to shake it!"


translate English day5_gr_T_5d057851:


    gg "That's actually counterproductive. Best to just leave it alone until the ink dries."


translate English day5_gr_T_4b317ec9:


    pl "Well, crap... It's a little blurry."


translate English day5_gr_T_2d618b87:


    gr "It's pretty good for a complete beginner. You set a good example for us to follow!"


translate English day5_gr_T_ccfc7753:


    pl "Huh? For who? What do you mean?"


translate English day5_gr_T_3aefb98e:


    gr "Exactly what I said. It's your turn to have your photos taken. Come on, [na2], look straight ahead!"


translate English day5_gr_T_2505c1ef:


    pl "Oh, no... This really is embarrassing!"


translate English day5_gr_T_aee9ce5c:


    nar "I've seen my reflection more than enough times in mirrors and puddles, but having my photo taken is something else altogether."


translate English day5_gr_T_c86dea7a:


    nar "Seeing a shot of yourself, frozen in time, is like looking at yourself through the eyes of a stranger."


translate English day5_gr_T_0859e285:


    nar "With my awkwardly stiff expression, I seem even darker, both in clothing and countenance, compared to the cheerful doctor sitting next to me. {w}This must be how other people see me on a regular basis."


translate English day5_gr_T_573b3ccb:


    gg "Mm, that came out pretty clear."


translate English day5_gr_T_8a08639c:


    pl "Yeah..."


translate English day5_gr_T_cc2b8b8b:


    gr "Wow, really? I feel like I look plumper than usual..."


translate English day5_gr_T_d3b8627e:


    gg "You look the same as always."


translate English day5_gr_T_ad8c458d:


    pl "You do eat sweets every day, doc."


translate English day5_gr_T_c1394a0f:


    gr "Well, my word! You two never stop!"


translate English day5_gr_T_16e5b9ae:


    nar "I wonder what keeping these photos means to her?"


translate English day5_gr_T_7fede7be:


    nar "This photo alone isn't enough for me to fully understand, though that doesn't mean I don't get it at all."


translate English day5_gr_T_0f06eded:


    nar "The photos we take are left, just like this, and in that way, we're able to keep a record of our memories to look back on later."


translate English day5_gr_T_157239a8:


    pl "Why the sudden desire to take this?"


translate English day5_gr_T_7d6e7ac7:


    gr "Because I wanted to give you this album, [na2]."


translate English day5_gr_T_bc123015:


    pl "Huh? You're giving me the album, too?"


translate English day5_gr_T_d434bd74:


    gr "Yes. And we can fill it with the memories you make here whenever you stop by."


translate English day5_gr_T_aafef7fe:


    gr "The memories we'll make together, whether happy, sad, cheerful, or worried."


translate English day5_gr_T_53a3c6c7:


    pl "There's no need to be so formal... {w}You know I'm an open book when it comes to talking with you about what's bothering me."


translate English day5_gr_T_50eea56a:


    gr "Really?"


translate English day5_gr_T_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "..."


translate English day5_gr_T_e9f6c0b2:


    gr "Goodness, you really trust us that much, [na2]? You know we're always here whenever you need us."


translate English day5_gr_T_c2cb424d:


    gr "You're putting so much effort into your work, and we want to support you as best we can."


translate English day5_gr_T_c4888bde:


    gr "You're always welcome to come back, whenever you want. {w}We can be the family that you never had."


translate English day5_gr_T_3d53eeb6:


    pl "Sure... I'll keep that in mind."


translate English day5_ar_T_c7e30961:


    br "\n When people think of the temple's Magic Department, Arnie and the department's stubborn-headed bishop generally come to mind.{w} But for the younger girls here especially, things are a little different.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_ar_T_c72f975e:


    extend "\n That being the man named Enoch Apis.{w} His unusually slender stature and youthful appearance are probably why you hear his name all over the temple.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_ar_T_f55bb1f4:


    extend "\n Another reason is probably that he commands the seat next to the girl no ordinary person can touch.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_ar_T_b557e357:


    extend "\n If Arnie is the protector of the bishop and priests, then Enoch has always seemed like he's wanted to protect Arnie.{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_ar_T_78ca499d:


    extend "\n After having grown close to the older sister and younger brother, they've talked my ear off about how much they care for each other{w}{nw}"


translate English day5_ar_T_e8e03122:


    extend "\nand how long they've been protecting each other."


translate English day5_ar_T_7f83a1c5:



    nvl clear
    br "\n If I sit quietly and listen to them reminiscing, it's funny how easily I come to understand how he first developed feelings for her, {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_ar_T_a10a34a3:


    extend "\nbut somewhere in my mind, I kind of pity him.{w} He's been working his ass off trying to accept me, {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_ar_T_903e5afd:


    extend "\nbut it seems to me like he's really leaning on his belief that he's still protecting half of her."


translate English day5_ar_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_ar_T_1e3f7b21:


    nar "Given how late it is, the training grounds are empty, devoid of the priests usually crowding the place."


translate English day5_ar_T_41584913:


    nar "The door is open, and the lights shine from the ceiling, but the grounds are so large that I'm scared of going in with nobody else present."


translate English day5_ar_T_28ee537d:


    nar "As I goose bumps cover my skin, I quietly move to the center."


translate English day5_ar_T_5bec4342:


    nar "It's so quiet that my footsteps would echo really loudly."


translate English day5_ar_T_a55faa5f:


    nar "Surprisingly, though, I start to hear a faint voice from the room that should be quiet."


translate English day5_ar_T_fe876c00:


    nar "I open the now-familiar interior door and immediately see Arnie, having just put a spoon into her mouth."


translate English day5_ar_T_a7ac4067:


    nar "Enoch sits with his arms folded, while she sits with something like boiled white rice in front of her."


translate English day5_ar_T_52d31a5c:


    nar "But they both stop what they're doing, seeming surprised I visited."


translate English day5_ar_T_284d9dff:


    pl "What's up? Eating something?"


translate English day5_ar_T_d5147d0c:


    ar "Well, no..."


translate English day5_ar_T_13309f0f:


    en "Hey, yes you are.{w} Here, have some water."


translate English day5_ar_T_488f1b31:


    ar "Right... My apologies."


translate English day5_ar_T_3fe7d007:


    nar "She takes the water from him and picks up her spoon again."


translate English day5_ar_T_5b39b27d:


    nar "But she glances in my direction several times, as though she can't focus on the meal."


translate English day5_ar_T_4f2d69dc:


    ar "...How do you fare?"


translate English day5_ar_T_eadc7ed4:


    pl "I'm fine. I, uh...{w} I would have thought the two of you'd be working."


translate English day5_ar_T_c30f5bc6:


    en "Yeah, we would have been, but today's kind of an exception. We're on standby until we get further orders from the bishop."


translate English day5_ar_T_f1817f4b:


    pl "Oh."


translate English day5_ar_T_914aac8c:


    nar "Arnie, who has averted her gaze from me, move her spoon more quickly this time, scraping some of the thick, white stuff off the bottom of her bowl."


translate English day5_ar_T_67ee5422:


    en "Hey, Sis, don't rush. You'll upset your stomach."


translate English day5_ar_T_c26dfcd4:


    ar "I'm well aware.{w} Ahem... I'm terribly sorry, Brother.{w} You've caught me at a rather embarrassing time."


translate English day5_ar_T_945e0514:


    pl "Hey, don't worry about me. Do you always eat at this time?"


translate English day5_ar_T_4e52aa33:


    ar "No. Normally, we all eat together at a set time each day..."


translate English day5_ar_T_9eaa2596:


    en "But she was late because of the time she spent visiting a certain someone in the ward."


translate English day5_ar_T_94b59555:


    ar "E-Enoch...! You don't need to go into details."


translate English day5_ar_T_7134993f:


    pl "Ah..."


translate English day5_ar_T_f90622d5:


    nar "Suddenly, I remember when I woke up."


translate English day5_ar_T_23733de3:


    nar "I was drifting between dream and reality at the time, but she was the one I saw first out of everyone else."


translate English day5_ar_T_8eac3dc1:


    nar "Since she didn't know when I'd wake up, was she waiting by my side that whole time to welcome me back to the waking world?"


translate English day5_ar_T_3a07a1a2:


    nar "Belatedly, my face starts to heat up."


translate English day5_ar_T_567dc9af:


    pl "Come on, Arnie. You can't miss mealtime like that..."


translate English day5_ar_T_a15efa50:


    ar "...I'm terribly sorry."


translate English day5_ar_T_1cbdd989:


    nar "Enoch, seeming a little fed up with the situation, sighs a little."


translate English day5_ar_T_09d4f7fa:


    pl "Anyway... There's something I've been curious about. Can I ask you?"


translate English day5_ar_T_8d017b2b:


    ar "Yes, by all means."


translate English day5_ar_T_239d9792:


    pl "What's that thing?"


translate English day5_ar_T_657a5faf:


    nar "I've been wondering about it ever since coming in here."


translate English day5_ar_T_68897cce:


    nar "Behind the sofa they're sitting are bouquets piled up in a heap. Within each of the colorful arrangements is a letter."


translate English day5_ar_T_fafcaa21:


    "{nw}"


translate English day5_ar_T_7dcffab3:


    en "W-Well... They were, er, addressed to her.{w} We'd normally clean them all up, but with everything going on today..."


translate English day5_ar_T_90511900:


    pl "Ha! I was just a little surprised since they're always so neat and tidy."


translate English day5_ar_T_5bd12a88:


    pl "Definitely feels like a lot to handle, though I guess it makes sense you'd be getting so many fan letters."


translate English day5_ar_T_165fd3ed:


    ar "Actually, those are all from my uncle."


translate English day5_ar_T_90465102:


    pl "Uh?"


translate English day5_ar_T_a6092869:


    ar "Apparently, he grew worried about me when I went to be with you, Brother, and sent them here."


translate English day5_ar_T_fcbadc1b:


    ar "As his niece, I'm very flattered that he would be this worried for me being gone for such a short time."


translate English day5_ar_T_7ebfea1b:


    en "I guess I can get the worrying, but I wish he'd put himself in my shoes. I'm the one who has to clean it all up, after all..."


translate English day5_ar_T_0264c607:


    pl "Could I read one?"


translate English day5_ar_T_ddf6ef82:


    ar "Certainly."


translate English day5_ar_T_c9661e8c:


    et "\n\n\n\n\n...\"My beloved Arne, it has been some time. Has all been well?" with slowdissolve


translate English day5_ar_T_586d138b:


    "The training grounds feel ever darker and colder without your presence."


translate English day5_ar_T_539f4920:


    "I already find myself growing nostalgic for your admirable smile...\"..."


translate English day5_ar_T_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_ar_T_52cd3b26:


    en "He does this even though he knows I'm right there reading them with her..."


translate English day5_ar_T_8a3783a3:


    ar "Well, it makes me happy..."


translate English day5_ar_T_9760b5a6:


    pl "Er...Let's get back on topic! You were in the middle of eating."


translate English day5_ar_T_0b8325af:


    ar "Yes. Because stamina forms the underpinning of everything, mages must not go without food."


translate English day5_ar_T_9323c761:


    pl "You say that, but your dinner seems a little plain. No side dishes?"


translate English day5_ar_T_7797a9a4:


    ar "Ah, this is a type of boiled rice called porridge."


translate English day5_ar_T_c11436e6:


    ar "It has long been called the miracle food because of how easily your body absorbs the nutrients."


translate English day5_ar_T_b2b20f8f:


    pl "Oh... I mean, it just looks like regular old oatmeal to me."


translate English day5_ar_T_c9b20215:


    en "You might not want to go there. Her love for porridge is truly something to behold.{w} It's practically religion for her now."


translate English day5_ar_T_3b83edfb:


    pl "Any particular reason for that?"


translate English day5_ar_T_055b1c83:


    en "She got this way from trying to fix her unbalanced diet when she was little."


translate English day5_ar_T_338cbc6b:


    pl "What on earth did she do...?"


translate English day5_ar_T_8fc7dec6:


    ar "The simplest reason I have a penchant for porridge is because it is a perfectly balanced meal."


translate English day5_ar_T_84c80cb7:


    ar "I would very much like to treat you to some one day, Brother [na2]."


translate English day5_ar_T_95965827:


    ar "O great and powerful Lord, we thank you for all your blessings.{w} Amen!"


translate English day5_ar_T_b38452f6:


    en "Oh, I'll clean it up for you."


translate English day5_ar_T_d955683f:


    ar "No, I shall do it.{w} You stay here and chat with Brother [na2]."


translate English day5_ar_T_ee500c4f:


    en "H-hweh?!"


translate English day5_ar_T_35586ad0:


    nar "Ignoring her brother's dumb noise, Arnie picks up her empty bowl and leaves the room."


translate English day5_ar_T_745ef3c1:


    nar "Where is she going? Outside the room are the training grounds.{w} As Enoch stares vacantly at the tightly shut door, he heaves another sigh."


translate English day5_ar_T_25620eaf:


    nar "This time, it's loud enough for me to hear well."


translate English day5_ar_T_63117d89:


    en "Haaaah... What does she want me to talk to you for?"


translate English day5_ar_T_d11fe843:


    pl "I mean, who cares? Isn't it good if we're all friends?"


translate English day5_ar_T_86a0abde:


    en "That's not what I meant..."


translate English day5_ar_T_4dab1573:


    pl "I'll be in the Magic Department soon too, after all."


translate English day5_ar_T_df4b8cd3:


    en "Oh, right, you're on your fifth day... Time sure flies, huh?"


translate English day5_ar_T_a834e7fd:


    pl "How come you sound so out of it today?"


translate English day5_ar_T_6a59388c:


    en "Eh? I'm not out of it."


translate English day5_ar_T_fb39ca88:


    pl "You're talking differently."


translate English day5_ar_T_6189f005:


    en "No I'm not..."


translate English day5_ar_T_d7f22c7a:


    pl "I got it! You finally got a chance to be alone with her again, but then I interrupted, and now you're sulking."


translate English day5_ar_T_0fb226e2:


    en "...That's really not it.{w} And I'm not out of it.{w} You're being weird..."


translate English day5_ar_T_ee86ea75:


    pl "There you go again!"


translate English day5_ar_T_23d79fce:


    nar "I feel a little bad about it, but I want to distract myself from all the crap in my head at the moment."


translate English day5_ar_T_023c63e9:


    nar "A lot happened today. What I need now is some pointless conversation and maybe a little information."


translate English day5_ar_T_ee6d2081:


    pl "Now that I think of it, does the Magic Department fight the Lost too?"


translate English day5_ar_T_437a0add:


    en "Nah, we mainly exorcise evil spirits...and repair the Pestis, I guess."


translate English day5_ar_T_0ffa84bf:


    pl "Right, right, I've heard that. Doesn't seem like a very physically demanding job...{w} So why do you train every day?"


translate English day5_ar_T_a2741c95:


    en "You need stamina just to run to wherever you're needed and also to use your sacred power."


translate English day5_ar_T_4772b714:


    en "Plus, the Magic Department teaches martial arts as a way to direct your flow of energy."


translate English day5_ar_T_67590c7d:


    en "Though it's a little different than what most people think of as martial arts, I guess."


translate English day5_ar_T_233249af:


    pl "Well, I'm most people, so I wouldn't get it just by hearing you talk about it, huh?"


translate English day5_ar_T_2ecbf1f1:


    en "I mean, you can't see it if you can't see the Pestis. Same with spells."


translate English day5_ar_T_79f58bad:


    pl "Are spells separate from martial arts?"


translate English day5_ar_T_54e06156:


    en "Normally it's almost too much for a person to just learn one of them, much less both at the same time. Sister's an exception..."


translate English day5_ar_T_de15696a:


    pl "So you two were different from the start, huh?"


translate English day5_ar_T_cc917f49:


    en "Even under the same roof, if you train differently, you'll end up with differences, right?"


translate English day5_ar_T_d9224103:


    en "She'd never leave her desk all day long, but one day, she started getting more interested in the stuff I was doing."


translate English day5_ar_T_ac42a41a:


    en "Naturally, she didn't stand a chance against me at first.{w} And this is embarrassing, since at the time, my body and mind were still too young..."


translate English day5_ar_T_4d57ead0:


    en "But somewhere deep down, I was looking down on her."


translate English day5_ar_T_a36b3722:


    pl "Then you didn't think the sheltered girl was being rude or anything by wanting to mimic what you were doing without knowing what it was?"


translate English day5_ar_T_9a253532:


    en "I guess there was a little of that, too."


translate English day5_ar_T_8768347e:


    en "But it only took a single moment for the whole thing to be flipped."


translate English day5_ar_T_ddbacb13:


    en "Actually, she literally flipped me--physically. And as my body flipped over, so did everything inside...{w} At least, that's what it felt like."


translate English day5_ar_T_3b858891:


    en "After that, I kind of got a new perspective on things."


translate English day5_ar_T_15b11641:


    en "I never had much talent in fighting, but even so, I decided I wanted to stand by her and serve her for the rest of my life."


translate English day5_ar_T_8a08639c:


    pl "Uh-huh..."


translate English day5_ar_T_a29d0ec2:


    en "Well, anyway, sorry for dragging this on.{w} Anyway, that's how incredible she is."


translate English day5_ar_T_67612519:


    en "So she's not only got first-rate skills as a magic caster, she's got first-rate martial arts skill too!"


translate English day5_ar_T_6c1103eb:


    en "All the priests in the Magic Department really respect her, and that's why we can strive so hard to improve every single day."


translate English day5_ar_T_ebc26a91:


    pl "Oh. I see..."


translate English day5_ar_T_c3cfbcf0:


    nar "The closed door opens again, and Arnie boldly strides back into the room."


translate English day5_ar_T_0e11e60a:


    ar "I apologize for stepping away. How was your chat?"


translate English day5_ar_T_6d8e9773:


    pl "Chat? All he did was brag about you."


translate English day5_ar_T_5db0b988:


    en "Urgh! Don't tell HER that!!!"


translate English day5_ar_T_bd1787f4:


    ar "Bragging about me? I'm honored.{w} But I won't be outdone."


translate English day5_ar_T_4f2678b6:


    ar "Perhaps I'll brag about my little brother to you now, Brother."


translate English day5_ar_T_6f28e971:


    en "I... Um, er..."


translate English day5_ar_T_b292a2a9:


    pl "Enough already...{w} More importantly, Arnie, show me that power of yours too."


translate English day5_ar_T_1fe5feb5:


    pl "He keeps going on and on about how strong you are, but you've never actually shown me. Now, I'm curious."


translate English day5_ar_T_d3f7181d:


    en "Look, I get how you feel, but we mages aren't out to misuse our techniques for vanity's sake, you know."


translate English day5_ar_T_add92fb8:


    en "Quit being so rude, alright?"


translate English day5_ar_T_7bbbfeef:


    ar "Oh, I don't mind."


translate English day5_ar_T_e8642613:


    en "But--"


translate English day5_ar_T_8f09f42e:


    ar "True trials only come when and where you don't expect them."


translate English day5_ar_T_40545bf5:


    ar "If a brother wishes it, then I, Arne Alternata, will accept."


translate English day5_ar_T_4e51ba97:


    pl "Cool!"


translate English day5_ar_T_8cb5d72e:


    ar "However, there is one small thing I would ask of you first."


translate English day5_ar_T_8647211b:


    ar "Brother [na2], I would like you to join me on the training grounds."


translate English day5_ar_T_38864aa1:


    nar "Our eyes go wide at the sudden suggestion."


translate English day5_ar_T_01820bfd:


    pl "Me?"


translate English day5_ar_T_c0ac4a94:


    ar "Yes.{w} And I do, of course, have one more condition."


translate English day5_ar_T_699464cd:


    ar "I shall defeat you using only my left thumb and index finger, Brother. You may use whatever means you feel you must."


translate English day5_ar_T_6a0ba3e7:


    pl "Whoa. Wait, didn't you just say mages don't strut their stuff just to look good? Do you think you're underestimating me, even just a little?"


translate English day5_ar_T_00fe6735:


    pl "I know you're confident, but isn't that a bit much?{w} Why don't we do this instead?"


translate English day5_ar_T_653dbc8f:


    pl "We'll spar, and the loser has to listen to one request from the winner.{w} Sound good?"


translate English day5_ar_T_baf46ad1:


    ar "I will gladly accept your conditions."


translate English day5_ar_T_5b034900:


    en "......"


translate English day5_ar_T_f6b14323:


    pl "Great. Just don't whine about it later!"


translate English day5_ar_T_96cd2ee9:


    nar "The two of us stand across from each other in the desolate training grounds."


translate English day5_ar_T_a0711bd7:


    pl "I'm feeling kind of bad about asking you to show off now, Arnie. I know you've gotta be busy."


translate English day5_ar_T_b40679e5:


    ar "Regardless of the situation, I am happy to have the chance to face off against you, Brother."


translate English day5_ar_T_7f4342df:


    en "Alright, you two. Take your positions, and..."


translate English day5_ar_T_ab2c4ce5:


    nar "Upon hearing the signal to start, I launch into a forward dash."


translate English day5_ar_T_a389eca0:


    nar "But then something weird happens.{w} Despite running straight ahead, all I actualy see is the high, golden ceiling."


translate English day5_ar_T_3af5e616:


    nar "The arrangement of decorative illumination glows enough to make me feel a little faint."


translate English day5_ar_T_59864699:


    nar "Suddenly, a hand enters my vision.{w} A straight, flat one--white under the light from the ceiling."


translate English day5_ar_T_498df798:


    nar "I grab that hand and pull myself to my feet."


translate English day5_ar_T_3b12203b:


    ar "Victory is mine, Brother."


translate English day5_ar_T_53a4ef0e:


    nar "On the other end of the hand, she offers a wide smile. Her clear voice brings me back to my senses."


translate English day5_ar_T_30013dc6:


    pl "Wh...Wha...?"


translate English day5_ar_T_fd69e2ff:


    en "Like she said, she won."


translate English day5_ar_T_60ed1e6e:


    pl "But that's--that happened way too fast! Did you seriously only use your finger and your thumb?" with sshake


translate English day5_ar_T_b948b62c:


    er "There were no lies or deceit present here."


translate English day5_ar_T_64967345:


    nar "The low male voice I haven't heard in a while sends a chill down my spine."


translate English day5_ar_T_883ff51a:


    nar "The two behind me bow to him as he wears an expression that looks so confident I half expect him to break out into applause."


translate English day5_ar_T_ef62f624:


    er "Martial arts were originally ways to train your stamina using only your body--no weapons."


translate English day5_ar_T_6ffad7cd:


    er "A practitioner first focuses on being alert and quick enough to restrain an opponent, and the longer they train, the more they build up that muscle memory."


translate English day5_ar_T_47dd7d58:


    er "You do not simply throw yourself bodily at the opponent to defeat them.{w} I see you've already begun disciplining him, Arne."


translate English day5_ar_T_f8e7e806:


    ar "I was simply showing him an example.{w} Welcome back, Uncle."


translate English day5_ar_T_9747c780:


    pl "Yo, Magic Academy Bishop. Been a while, huh?"


translate English day5_ar_T_09733c42:


    en "WHAT?! Speak more respectfully to the bishop!"


translate English day5_ar_T_cc30b964:


    pl "You're all saying \"discipline\" and \"examples,\" but she was just toying with me."


translate English day5_ar_T_9db250b4:


    ar "Oh, I would never."


translate English day5_ar_T_1ff85e01:


    ar "As he suggests, I have only given you a first-hand lesson of what martial arts are and how they're used."


translate English day5_ar_T_f4d21947:


    ar "Many things cannot be explained with mere words.{w} And you did express an interest in my abilities."


translate English day5_ar_T_62e82abd:


    en "You get it now, right? The skills we mages polish are pretty serious stuff."


translate English day5_ar_T_8ce70d59:


    en "It's not supposed to be shown off to others for simple entertainment."


translate English day5_ar_T_84c5ae31:


    pl "I get it, I get it! I lost, and I admit it."


translate English day5_ar_T_35723a70:


    pl "If the bishop is here, does that mean I should get going?"


translate English day5_ar_T_5f9db8f0:


    er "Because the Magic Department's duties are assigned to its members based on their individual abilities, we welcome complete newcomers."


translate English day5_ar_T_a8e0c555:


    er "As this is a good opportunity, why don't we all enjoy some tea? Think of it as an early welcoming ceremony."


translate English day5_ar_T_d5240816:


    nar "The room's mood, which was light and jovial before, feels so much more grave whenever he talks."


translate English day5_ar_T_fb5f3b84:


    nar "The two of them deftly remove the white cloths from the tea cups."


translate English day5_ar_T_25102034:


    nar "They're perfectly clean without a hint of dust--maybe they're used regularly."


translate English day5_ar_T_a0ffed09:


    nar "After a few moments, they pour an almost strangely red liquid into the teacup in front of me, causing steam to rise from the low table."


translate English day5_ar_T_d6d05cba:


    nar "Being here is awkward and I'm not used to the smells of tea, so this is rough for me."


translate English day5_ar_T_d7781885:


    er "What is it? Do you not like tea?"


translate English day5_ar_T_124684b1:


    pl "I just haven't ever really drank it much."


translate English day5_ar_T_65a7641c:


    er "Then it isn't just that you find this situation uncomfortable?"


translate English day5_ar_T_b513491e:


    nar "And now he's being overly considerate."


translate English day5_ar_T_a46ed90e:


    nar "I mess with my fingers under the table, growing irritated, as Arnie takes a seat next to me, having filled all four of the cups on the table."


translate English day5_ar_T_9d2bf247:


    nar "This time, my heart skips a beat for a different reason.{w} The sight of the three of them, who look so much alike, all sitting down with each other would probably strike just about anyone as strange."


translate English day5_ar_T_5cf50c5a:


    er "No need for someone as young as you to be so stiff. You needn't act so formally. After all, you are about to become part of the Magic Department's family."


translate English day5_ar_T_9cabc7c1:


    pl "Hahaha... I'm serious--that isn't it. Do you three have tea like this a lot?"


translate English day5_ar_T_fd17c8bc:


    er "It is somewhat more rare now because of our work schedules growing busy, but we do try to as much as possible."


translate English day5_ar_T_b10870cf:


    er "Arne, your skill at brewing tea is next to none."


translate English day5_ar_T_4c4dc3ae:


    en "I was right there helping her too, you know..."


translate English day5_ar_T_13881efb:


    er "Don't be fussy.{w} I know you were--naturally."


translate English day5_ar_T_29a775d6:


    en "Right..."


translate English day5_ar_T_e28f9f46:


    er "That aside.{w} [na], I've heard you lingered on the border of life and death today. How are you feeling?"


translate English day5_ar_T_6c1d3c03:


    pl "Fine, I guess. The injuries are all healed."


translate English day5_ar_T_f10c0946:


    er "Are they, now?"


translate English day5_ar_T_2d447b53:


    pl "I guess you've heard everything, huh?{w} What are your thoughts on this scar?"


translate English day5_ar_T_9ba6cbd2:


    pl "Bishops have huge brains, right? You know something about it, don't you?"


translate English day5_ar_T_a1058a89:


    er "You refer to the mark on your arm.{w} I, too, believe it must be a sign of a revelation."


translate English day5_ar_T_2384a1f9:


    nar "The two others listening in silence put their cups down at the same time."


translate English day5_ar_T_aeba4b1a:


    pl "The Academics Department bishop was saying the same thing. But what's a \"revelation\" or whatever, anyway?"


translate English day5_ar_T_2a9f9e4c:


    er "In essence, we believe God is attempting to deliver a message to humanity via your body."


translate English day5_ar_T_7963ba5a:


    er "Such revelations are the only evidence we have that God has not yet abandoned us or these lands."


translate English day5_ar_T_1a33b8af:


    er "We mages have long foretold these revelations."


translate English day5_ar_T_6081c9d8:


    pl "You...foretold them?"


translate English day5_ar_T_4ebcc242:


    en "Mages have got a whole bunch of different abilities.{w} Our family in particular have been prophets for a long time."


translate English day5_ar_T_3152c564:


    er "You mustn't interrupt us, Enoch.{w} You truly cannot help yourself when the topic at hand is related to you, can you?"


translate English day5_ar_T_765f3622:


    en "Bishop, you only ever call me when you need me.{w} You're gonna get real dependent on me soon if you keep going!"


translate English day5_ar_T_5d2d7273:


    er "That is correct!{w} I've learned to use you efficiently--I could leave you alone, and you would still serve some use."


translate English day5_ar_T_14cf70d1:


    ar "Enoch was also the one who found you, Brother, out of all those descended from mages."


translate English day5_ar_T_80888342:


    pl "Wait, really?"


translate English day5_ar_T_aa6227dc:


    er "Indeed.{w} God has deigned to choose you to become a new member of the Alternata family."


translate English day5_ar_T_be3bc642:


    er "Add that to the scars engraved into you on this day. I very much doubt this is mere coincidence."


translate English day5_ar_T_74c5b7e7:


    pl "But... Prophecies don't hold much water until they actually give results, you know?"


translate English day5_ar_T_8ab6d6ec:


    er "Just as winners and losers are determined from the outset and one's lifespan determines whether one will die at a young age,"


translate English day5_ar_T_fa81f803:


    er "fate is not something to be suddenly changed one day--it is something that simply is, and always has been."


translate English day5_ar_T_eea9e2c0:


    er "The only difference is that prophets are able to see that."


translate English day5_ar_T_0e367b80:


    pl "Huh, that's crazy. Prophets really exist, then, huh?"


translate English day5_ar_T_8fe36361:


    ar "The temple is home to many. Their jobs include both predicting calamities and receiving divine revelations."


translate English day5_ar_T_26f3b402:


    ar "The Academics Department's past records and research have been an incredible aid in resolving the Pestis, but the prophecies do so in different ways."


translate English day5_ar_T_c7dfdfe2:


    er "Indeed. Their techniques are as child's play--pitiful before the power of our prophecies."


translate English day5_ar_T_75fd84a4:


    er "We mage-prophets hear the voice of God through our strong sense of faith and sacred power. It is our job to convey His will to others."


translate English day5_ar_T_76ab202e:


    pl "Huh... Then Enoch here is actually a real big deal with the mages!{w} Wait, then why do you keep busy doing all this stuff?"


translate English day5_ar_T_b5133996:


    en "Because I never had any talent. Otherwise, I wouldn't be staring at horse's asses at the racecourse every day! Ha ha ha!"


translate English day5_ar_T_163fa21f:


    er "Self-deprecation ill befits a priest of our department, Enoch. Especially one I personally chose."


translate English day5_ar_T_45f848d7:


    en "Yeah. You're right, of course."


translate English day5_ar_T_9cbfb178:


    en "Didn't mean to fish for comfort. Now I'm embarrassed..."


translate English day5_ar_T_06761731:


    pl "Well, it's pretty obvious you three have known each other your whole lives."


translate English day5_ar_T_609f3f74:


    pl "Hold on. Then where's your father, Arnie? The bishop's your uncle, right?"


translate English day5_ar_T_057ceb35:


    ar "My parents both ascended to Heaven when I was very young.{w} My uncle took me in when I had nowhere else to go."


translate English day5_ar_T_676135bc:


    ar "He gave value to a wanderer and illuminated the path of life for her."


translate English day5_ar_T_b6b35e69:


    er "Mm. I've loved Arne as my own ever since then."


translate English day5_ar_T_9bfb580d:


    pl "Then what about you, Enoch?{w} You...well, you couldn't be the bishop's actual son, I guess.{w} Bit of a height issue there."


translate English day5_ar_T_21439334:


    en "Nah, of course not.{w} Just look at how different our sizes are!{w} But yeah, Arnie and I were in similar circumstances."


translate English day5_ar_T_ade66246:


    en "I seriously had zero talent, so I couldn't even really call myself a mage.{w} That's why the head of my family abandoned me."


translate English day5_ar_T_f65f3bf6:


    er "And that's why I took you in.{w} I had just been looking for someone to write down winning lottery numbers for me."


translate English day5_ar_T_0b48794e:


    er "You were so friendly and polite back then."


translate English day5_ar_T_97f7a366:


    ar "Thanks to my uncle's consideration, I lived as a child free of loneliness and solitude."


translate English day5_ar_T_f04c49fd:


    er "Ahem. In any case, what I'm trying to say is that everyone has their uses."


translate English day5_ar_T_11e4ff9d:


    er "Some out there will make excuses like, \"I lacked talent, so it's hopeles\" or \"it's fate, so it's hopeless,"


translate English day5_ar_T_04cc069a:


    er "and accept a life not unlike that of the dead. However, those are all complaints of a loser."


translate English day5_ar_T_ab8d0a55:


    pl "But didn't you just say fate can't be changed?"


translate English day5_ar_T_a693339a:


    er "A fate set in stone cannot be easily changed, of course.{w} But fate will always take the hands of those who live until the very end."


translate English day5_ar_T_295c0cca:


    er "It does not change then and there--it was fated to change, right from the start."


translate English day5_ar_T_f2321f77:


    er "That is why, even if we must crawl through this hell, we must fulfill our duty to survive."


translate English day5_ar_T_c2a41a22:


    er "I believe in the day that fate will take my hand..."


translate English day5_ar_T_8b1c3fb9:


    er "-Yet there are some things that still cannot be changed no matter how much we struggle. That is why life is cruel."


translate English day5_ar_T_4f60fdf8:


    er "Just like how every eldest Alternata child dies young--a reminder and a revelation of the unchanging nature of fate."


translate English day5_ar_T_b9a00e98:


    pl "...They die young?"


translate English day5_ar_T_3e04d823:


    ar "It is a form of revelation that has continually been conveyed to us for a very, very long time."


translate English day5_ar_T_a9877fd2:


    ar "My mother was the oldest of three siblings--an older sister to Uncle--and so she ascended to Heaven when I was very young."


translate English day5_ar_T_eb1e660c:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_ar_T_97e46fcb:


    pl "Does this all mean you know everything that's going to happen from now on, Bishop?"


translate English day5_ar_T_15633a6d:


    er "Of course not.{w} My ultimate fate is simply to serve God, and no amount of struggling, writhing, or back-breaking effort will change that."


translate English day5_ar_T_ea553ea3:


    er "Even I grow uneasy at times.{w} And even I have my fair share of worries, troubles, and regrets."


translate English day5_ar_T_683f03dc:


    er "If I had that sort of power, then my younger brother would never have been killed by that bastard calling himself cardinal!" with sshake


translate English day5_ar_T_2e140b8c:


    nar "Suddenly enraged by the conversation, the calm Bishop Erzsebet erupts into anger, slamming the table."


translate English day5_ar_T_f42e8d68:


    nar "Arnie, sitting next to me, calmly cleans up the droplets of tea that flew from the teacups.{w} The bishop quickly massages his temples with a hand and heaves a sigh."


translate English day5_ar_T_75e23002:


    er "[na], how much do you know of this temple's cardinal?"


translate English day5_ar_T_8238a8a9:


    pl "I know that he's Bishop Haku's father, and that he established the Cleaning Department."


translate English day5_ar_T_60d60093:


    er "My younger brother had been close friends with him for a very long time."


translate English day5_ar_T_82d956aa:


    er "Because the one to assume the seat of cardinal is generally a mage, everyone expected my brother to become the next cardinal."


translate English day5_ar_T_cdba54d0:


    er "I expected him to as well.{w} Honestly, I was very proud of having a brother like him."


translate English day5_ar_T_d2d6596c:


    er "But it wasn't to be.{w} My brother died, and that bastard crawled up into the cardinal's seat instead."


translate English day5_ar_T_4cb930b1:


    pl "Wait, you make it sound like a coincidence."


translate English day5_ar_T_8dc267da:


    pl "According to you, the cardinal getting a divine revelation was his fate to begin with, right?"


translate English day5_ar_T_b8a4c7f8:


    er "That brute? A divine revelation?{w} HAH! Laughable."


translate English day5_ar_T_b1081635:


    er "Him? A spokesman for God when he himself is an insult to morality and discipline?{w} A walking calamity wearing human skin?"


translate English day5_ar_T_2443d071:


    er "If that's what fate is, then I swear I will stop wiping the ass of this jerk of a god!" with sshake


translate English day5_ar_T_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_ar_T_0ee191c8:


    nar "I can't even manage a grunt in response to his powerful declaration.{w} I just aimlessly fiddle with my teacup."


translate English day5_ar_T_000205dc:


    er "He has sullied the name of God and stolen everything from me.{w} I have risked everything to protect what little I have left."


translate English day5_ar_T_9d2d1910:


    er "My time, my honor, even my remaining life--I've put it all on the line.{w} Before long, he will invite disaster and become a threat to this entire continent."


translate English day5_ar_T_af06bb09:


    er "I will NOT allow his schemes to come to fruition. I WILL survive."


translate English day5_ar_T_7f052818:


    er "And then I will prove to him that fate has always been on my side."


translate English day5_ar_T_25cdae28:


    er "Life never goes as one expects, but it is in ceaseless rejection of that endless chain that humans assert their humanity."


translate English day5_ar_T_3ca4f15d:


    er "[na], Arne is all I have left."


translate English day5_ar_T_0fbaabfc:


    er "I didn't want to simply wait for fate to take away this girl's future--this girl my younger brother left behind."


translate English day5_ar_T_ae99f3c1:


    er "I need you for this.{w} No matter what happens, I will protect my seedlings.{w} And I am proud to call you one of them."


translate English day5_ar_T_0f70625d:


    er "As you say, we will only know who emerges victorious from the result, but I want to take a risk on you."


translate English day5_ar_T_35d7a808:


    er "For the sake of mankind's future, wounded by the cardinal as it has been--and for my beloved Arne's fate."


translate English day5_ar_T_9327a101:


    nar "Their grave expressions all settle on me.{w} It feels like they've taken away any chance I had to flee."


translate English day5_ar_T_a64b51d2:


    nar "My tea has long since gone cold; I haven't taken a single sip of it."


translate English day5_ar_T_339da3d0:


    pl "...I need to go out for some air."


translate English day5_ar_T_80609269:


    nar "I leave the place at a sprint.{w} I'm running from the weight of this burden."


translate English day5_ar_T_d0ef5911:


    nar "Maybe I should get my thoughts in order."


translate English day5_ar_T_1417151e:


    nar "I leave the building, then fill my lungs with the outside air that has heard nothing about what happened inside.{w} My brain isn't working."


translate English day5_ar_T_f39ef99c:


    nar "I only wanted to go see Arnie.{w} How did I end up sitting through an unwanted speech from that dirty old fart of a man?"


translate English day5_ar_T_c459c822:


    nar "All of it feels like something I never should have found out about."


translate English day5_ar_T_8fb8aa7b:


    nar "But they claimed it was all something I needed to know."


translate English day5_ar_T_d25dc02d:


    nar "If I'm lacking something, then what is it that's missing?{w} The resolve to become part of their family?{w} The courage to get closer to the truth?"


translate English day5_ar_T_55915cf6:


    nar "The right to be with her--or the ability to confront her?"


translate English day5_ar_T_c1def52c:


    nar "I'm missing more than one thing.{w} Compared to her, I'm miserable--I lack just about everything."


translate English day5_ar_T_c01b246b:


    en "Hey, man. Don't run out like that.{w} You sure gave us a scare!"


translate English day5_ar_T_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_ar_T_57e79b45:


    en "I know you're probably in shock about finding all that stuff out all of a sudden, but you don't need to worry about it so much."


translate English day5_ar_T_9e2e8da1:


    en "The bishop is just trying to explain how much he likes you--"


translate English day5_ar_T_6105f543:


    pl "You didn't need to come find me. I was going to head back inside in a few minutes."


translate English day5_ar_T_d00dfd86:


    pl "Besides, wouldn't it be better for you if I just left and never came back?"


translate English day5_ar_T_5431870d:


    en "What?"


translate English day5_ar_T_181e5ed6:


    pl "Come on. You were just flaunting that time you were spending with her today without me--again."


translate English day5_ar_T_0bc7a9bd:


    pl "Why wouldn't I want to ask about that?"


translate English day5_ar_T_04b1f5d3:


    pl "But it seems to me you're still too trapped by your memories of those days."


translate English day5_ar_T_69d12724:


    pl "And why's that? Since you thought Arnie might die because of that revelation?"


translate English day5_ar_T_6fc44b39:


    en "Right...{w} You seem like you're just venting here, [na], but..."


translate English day5_ar_T_11bc0cd7:


    pl "All you wanted to do was deny it, right?"


translate English day5_ar_T_8093664a:


    pl "You can't STAND the fact that a guy like me is marrying someone so important to you!"


translate English day5_ar_T_4fce8d60:


    pl "That's why you want to go back to the days when she belonged to you."


translate English day5_ar_T_5b034900_1:


    en "......"


translate English day5_ar_T_a6e44a09:


    pl "I hate that shit."


translate English day5_ar_T_fb1d8802:


    pl "If you really loved her, you wouldn't be lashing out at me--you'd be grabbing her and running the hell away from this cramped, old place!"


translate English day5_ar_T_669ee2c7:


    pl "You locked her up when she was little because you were scared of her getting hurt, and now you're leaving her future in the hands of some random outsider?"


translate English day5_ar_T_edf10086:


    pl "And don't you dare say it's all for her or whatever!{w} You're just being a coward!"


translate English day5_ar_T_6af08f0a:


    en "You sure do act like you know a lot about it.{w} But I think you're the one lashing out here."


translate English day5_ar_T_1609446e:


    en "My feelings for her aren't the cheap little puppy love you seem to have."


translate English day5_ar_T_c298b9c7:


    en "I've looked up to her for almost as long as I can remember.{w} I would do *anything* to make sure she has a happy life."


translate English day5_ar_T_613055af:


    pl "Then why can't you be honest with me instead of just being jealous all the time?!"


translate English day5_ar_T_a44a6f04:


    en "Because that's not what she wants!!!{w} I don't want to force my selfish wishes down her throat." with sshake


translate English day5_ar_T_32433035:


    en "I want her to grow into someone who can decide for herself what she wants to do.{w} But even that's me being selfish..."


translate English day5_ar_T_b46570e6:


    en "If she wants to be with you, then I'm fully prepared to celebrate that."


translate English day5_ar_T_5d09dd53:


    en "Because it would make her happy.{w} And you call me jealous?{w} You say I'M trapped by the past?"


translate English day5_ar_T_919067a1:


    en "That only goes to show that you don't understand even a little of her determination."


translate English day5_ar_T_eb1e660c_3:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_ar_T_9fa84cef:


    en "So please.{w} For her sake, get your head screwed back on straight and take this seriously."


translate English day5_ar_T_a4dc04a1:


    en "In all honesty, I didn't want you to end up with such a heavy burden either."


translate English day5_ar_T_9522743e:


    en "But the bishop chose you--God Above chose you.{w} I'm nothing more than a normal person, and yet..." with sshake


translate English day5_ar_T_438d1924:


    en "I'm working so hard so that you can be part of her family in a real way."


translate English day5_ar_T_80743447:


    nar "My stomach hurts."


translate English day5_ar_T_dbddb4c8:


    en "You can go home now if you want. I don't care...{w} I know you've gotta be worn out from those wounds. I'm sorry."


translate English day5_ar_T_a4e1832d:


    nar "Left alone in the silence, I grip the cold wall with my hands and vomit." with sshake


translate English day5_ar_T_2a9d9fff:


    nar "I haven't eaten anything today, so the liquid spewing from my throat is whitish and clear--digested things from yesterday or the day before."


translate English day5_ar_T_7b086b3e:


    nar "With the liquid going back into my nose after that, my throat continues to clench and my stomach continues to heave."


translate English day5_ar_T_63cef6c2:


    nar "Enoch didn't even raise his voice.{w} Doesn't that mean he's just scared of taking responsibility for her life and making their family his enemy?"


translate English day5_ar_T_dcd0b9d5:


    nar "But he doesn't have the ability to do so, so when the bishop brought me in, he accepted me."


translate English day5_ar_T_4c1d2bbc:


    nar "And now he's just accepted the situation, too, where all he can do is hope in vain, like he has been this whole time."


translate English day5_ar_T_6d0c4ea5:


    nar "So what about me?{w} Why isn't anyone asking ME how I feel about this?"


translate English day5_ar_T_08bde79c:


    nar "As the vomitus and spit drips from my chin, I glare up at the still-yellow sky."


translate English day5_ar_T_d5802aaf:


    ar "Brother [na2]."


translate English day5_ar_T_a000bfe8:


    nar "The hand that once gripped my hand now holds my shoulder.{w} My vision and mind are still blurry since I haven't taken a genuine breath in a while."


translate English day5_ar_T_785210bf:


    nar "I try to say something, but the only things that come up are sour-tasting vomit--again--and hacking coughs.{w} Then, a perfectly clean cloth touches my filthy face."


translate English day5_ar_T_ddf82712:


    nar "Arnie wouldn't have a handkerchief--is it her clothes?{w} My mind is so slow right now that I can't figure out what the situation is."


translate English day5_ar_T_47a2a119:


    ar "It's alright.{w} You don't need to think about anything...{w} This isn't a problem you should be concerned over, Brother."


translate English day5_ar_T_f7d5aad8:


    nar "Her voice is so comforting that it almost carries all my worries away.{w} I'm envious of them.{w} They've been relying on this voice of hers for so long now."


translate English day5_ar_T_eb1f0279:


    nar "All I've been doing is forcing my own desires and values on her--it's like I've never even asked her thoughts on it."


translate English day5_ar_T_cc9980dd:


    nar "But I do know the reason for it, albeit vaguely."


translate English day5_ar_T_97e29478:


    nar "She can put me first in her mind because she trusts those around her to support her ideas and decisions."


translate English day5_ar_T_1144f908:


    nar "I don't have that level of resolve.{w} That's why I scorned the walls of goodwill surrounding her.{w} Could there be anything more shameful?"


translate English day5_ar_T_297c83fa:


    ar "Once you've calmed down a little, I'll bring you back to your dormitory."


translate English day5_ar_T_b67b39d4:


    nar "What is Arnie actually thinking?{w} Is this sort of thing just going to keep happening, over and over?"


translate English day5_ar_T_740d631f:


    nar "I want nothing more than to ask her true feelings on the matter, but the coughing won't stop."


translate English day5_rs_T_fd539f46:


    br "\n At some point, I'd started focusing more on finding proof that she isn't human rather than finding proof that she *is*. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_45760e22:


    extend "\nI'm not a big fan of awkwardly staring, but she's looked at me just as much as I look at her. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_1f4eb40a:


    extend "\nI'm basically always watching her, but when I'm not, she's watching me. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_1e5bedb7:


    extend "\nSo for each of us, the other naturally became a target of observation. Those dark eyes of hers... {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_8647ff32:


    extend "\nLike fish drifting in rust-colored seas among impure bubbles, her empty eyes simply glowed as she observed me without blinking at all."


translate English day5_rs_T_3460256c:



    nvl clear
    br "\n One day, I find her in the corner of a room, quietly putting her fingertips into her mouth. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_69e6a7ba:


    extend "\nShe's been doing that without a sound for a long time now without me realizing. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_6efed536:


    extend "\nAll five of her fingers--nails nearly torn off, but still holding fast--are covered in drool and a little bit of blood. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_814cb720:


    extend "\nEven after that, several times, I found her doing something similar while I observed her, but this time, she strangely took the finger back out right away and rolled her tongue over it. {w}{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_7a71d5ac:


    extend "\nUpon closer inspection, her ten nails are slathered in a clear medicine. {w} I decided to overlook it."


translate English day5_rs_T_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day5_rs_T_3f576d59:


    nar "I step into the library, wondering if I'd run into Lavien, but once again, nobody is around."


translate English day5_rs_T_3985d4ee:


    nar "While not being able to see anyone is par for the course, it's past lunchtime today."


translate English day5_rs_T_f284ac0f:


    nar "Everyone must have just started their afternoon work. I can't even sense anyone's presence nearby."


translate English day5_rs_T_d90ccba3:


    ev "Is there a book you're looking for...?"


translate English day5_rs_T_e7c753eb:


    nar "And in that quiet space, a cold hand softly touches my relaxed shoulder."


translate English day5_rs_T_59da0e39:


    nar "Hearing the cold voice that seems to slither up to the crown of my head freezes my spine solid for a moment."


translate English day5_rs_T_20ff22ab:


    nar "This is the one person I didn't want to run into..."


translate English day5_rs_T_84496844:


    pl "Hey, so... Could you not show up behind me like that?"


translate English day5_rs_T_d0978ba9:


    ev "Hee hee hee... But it's one of my very few hobbies."


translate English day5_rs_T_11b9d144:


    ev "People will generally keep their eyes forward and claim they understand everything about themselves."


translate English day5_rs_T_bed590b9:


    ev "But the truest emotions appear from behind as well as from in front."


translate English day5_rs_T_8cde2889:


    ev "Just like the hairs sticking up on the back of your neck right now, Brother. Hee hee heeee..."


translate English day5_rs_T_1a23916e:


    nar "My hand goes up to cover the back of my head--and the goosebumps on it.{w} But apparently my doing so is funny to her yet again."


translate English day5_rs_T_e75d87ae:


    pl "I'm surprised you're here at this hour, Bishop.{w} Are you already done working?"


translate English day5_rs_T_56c77097:


    ev "Oh, no, that would not be allowed.{w} But everyone needs breaks."


translate English day5_rs_T_6fe44c2e:


    pl "Come to think of it, you were the only one not there when I first met all the bishops..."


translate English day5_rs_T_7706d661:


    pl "Is it okay for you to do stuff like that without batting an eyelid, Bishop?"


translate English day5_rs_T_06dcf08a:


    ev "Please, call me Evelynn.{w} I far prefer that to Bishop."


translate English day5_rs_T_d0032977:


    nar "Suddenly, without warning, she brings her face close to mine.{w} The thick, cloying scent of flowers makes me catch my breath."


translate English day5_rs_T_46aeac53:


    nar "It's not the scent of the library--it's coming directly from her."


translate English day5_rs_T_46719d37:


    pl "Right... Okay, Lady Evelynn."


translate English day5_rs_T_fa58aa5f:


    nar "Seeming satisfied with my answer, she straightens back up and smiles."


translate English day5_rs_T_d51321b8:


    nar "Geez, nobody in the Academics Department has any sense of personal space..."


translate English day5_rs_T_3bb0175b:


    ev "Knowing one another's name gives us a bond that connects us."


translate English day5_rs_T_a1940747:


    pl "Is that magic-related too or something?"


translate English day5_rs_T_fc7f81d5:


    ev "Do you remember the words I gave you when we first met?"


translate English day5_rs_T_c0521f6f:


    pl "Hmm... What were they again?{w} Something about God..."


translate English day5_rs_T_20b93794:


    ev "Creating ties between knots--specifically people--is also part of God's will.{w} Thus, this world has no coincidences."


translate English day5_rs_T_e2808a73:


    ev "It must have been fate that you visited this place on that day."


translate English day5_rs_T_e7bf8dd4:


    ev "Each of the other encounters you've experienced, too, have their own reasons behind them..."


translate English day5_rs_T_9ca9f09b:


    ev "And so I thank God for giving me the chance to meet you on this wonderful day."


translate English day5_rs_T_18c1111b:


    pl "I don't mind you thanking God or whatever, but I'd appreciate a little thanks for me for coming all the way here."


translate English day5_rs_T_1e90ca5b:


    ev "Oh, of course.{w} How are you feeling?"


translate English day5_rs_T_e2073aa0:


    pl "I'm fine. No real problems here."


translate English day5_rs_T_d9a1fc86:


    ev "Hmm..."


translate English day5_rs_T_a92c7829:


    nar "She gives me those annoying, hateful eyes again.{w} It's always unpleasant, no matter how many times she looks at me with those carefully appraising eyes."


translate English day5_rs_T_1352b564:


    ev "I'm glad to hear it."


translate English day5_rs_T_00c8214e:


    pl "Err, about before...{w} What did you mean by an audience with God?"


translate English day5_rs_T_6846d28e:


    ev "I am honored to hear you ask that question, Brother.{w} God Himself has \"personally\" given you those wounds."


translate English day5_rs_T_948f8534:


    pl "Um. So that means... Well, what exactly does it mean?"


translate English day5_rs_T_21406e15:


    pl "Are you saying everything was fate--the Pestis suddenly moving then me running into a Lost and getting injured?"


translate English day5_rs_T_e77fa72a:


    ev "You understand--splendid! Truly splendid.{w} To go into even more fascinating detail, I have been studying the Pestis with this department for a long time."


translate English day5_rs_T_f5a46e6b:


    ev "I've also long researched God's stigmata in my own way.{w} But your body is particularly exceptional."


translate English day5_rs_T_974f9c2c:


    ev "It is as though God is trying to tell us something by using your body as a medium..."


translate English day5_rs_T_6079d9cf:


    ev "To the point where I am honored to no end that I was able to see something like it during my lifetime."


translate English day5_rs_T_1089eb5d:


    pl "Still doesn't really make sense to me..."


translate English day5_rs_T_4c9cb0ce:


    ev "I know it's hard to accept.{w} But I cannot say anything more."


translate English day5_rs_T_805710e0:


    ev "After all, your body belongs to you--as does its miracle..."


translate English day5_rs_T_5d71656c:


    ev "Should it come to pass that a similar phenomenon appears in the future, I would very much so like you at my side."


translate English day5_rs_T_f4836682:


    pl "Hey, Lady Eveylnn... You're not very good friends with the Health Department bishop, are you?"


translate English day5_rs_T_89876926:


    ev "Hee hee hee! That couldn't be further from the truth.{w} We are long-time friends.{w} I've gotten to know plenty of people in my time."


translate English day5_rs_T_eb1e660c:


    pl "......"


translate English day5_rs_T_385c6ce3:


    ev "Oh, but I suppose that's hard to believe, coming from me."


translate English day5_rs_T_e057fca4:


    pl "N-No, it's not...!{w} But you had a little fight with him in the ward before, didn't you?"


translate English day5_rs_T_fd6df219:


    ev "I should think arguing over matters of opinion is one of the abilities afforded to friends."


translate English day5_rs_T_d9ff1db3:


    ev "I was simply a little curious--yes, very slightly curious."


translate English day5_rs_T_9298b5e1:


    pl "Well, I get the curiosity, I guess.{w} Not the other stuff, though."


translate English day5_rs_T_6b9719f8:


    ev "Indeed. You're very curious yourself, aren't you, Brother [na]?{w} It's very important for people like us to get a very good look at what's around us."


translate English day5_rs_T_bea5956e:


    ev "The magical power created by such curiosity is very powerful and tends to attract others."


translate English day5_rs_T_20a7cf7b:


    ev "And if that happens, you will lose sight of your connections--and of yourself."


translate English day5_rs_T_cad4c674:


    pl "I'll keep that in mind.{w} I've still got logic and morals, though, so no need to worry."


translate English day5_rs_T_af48cdd7:


    ev "Logic and morals... Yes, that is well.{w} Morals are like coffins that keep people trapped inside."


translate English day5_rs_T_337efbf2:


    ev "They are shackles that maintain our humanity by locking out possibilities that break away from the norm."


translate English day5_rs_T_1b02b3dd:


    ev "As long as your sense of reason protects those shackles, both you and the connections you maintain will be safe and secure."


translate English day5_rs_T_0b7fab31:


    pl "You've been saying stuff like that a lot.{w} Did you go through something similar?"


translate English day5_rs_T_1a370bb5:


    ev "Hee hee heeee. At times, there are bonds that we cannot explain to others."


translate English day5_rs_T_a8ce2c92:


    ev "Oh, and the book you're looking for is over there."


translate English day5_rs_T_3e7b936d:


    nar "Lady Evelynn slightly twists to show me the door behind her.{w} That's Rose's room."


translate English day5_rs_T_25861082:


    pl "You knew?"


translate English day5_rs_T_beba9dc0:


    ev "I, too, have a deep connection to her."


translate English day5_rs_T_0a9e4678:


    pl "Umm... Then do you know things about her I don't?"


translate English day5_rs_T_333902f2:


    ev "About our clunky princess, you mean?"


translate English day5_rs_T_f7d4c6c7:


    pl "...That's kind of a mean way to put it, isn't it?"


translate English day5_rs_T_e1161b89:


    ev "Heh, I think it's cute."


translate English day5_rs_T_184d193f:


    nar "I see. Like Lavi said at first, there are plenty of people asking about her..."


translate English day5_rs_T_eb63bfd9:


    nar "And after all, I've seen quite a few people coming and going from that room..."


translate English day5_rs_T_e1c9d912:


    nar "It wasn't something I particularly wanted to keep secret, but for some reason I'm a little dis--{nw}"


translate English day5_rs_T_fff7b4e4:


    ev "Nobody else knows."


translate English day5_rs_T_bc16b943:


    nar "...She read my mind."


translate English day5_rs_T_37344452:


    ev "Nobody else knows.{w} If you don't tell anyone else...then the secret will be protected forever."


translate English day5_rs_T_304c61a8:


    pl "No... I wasn't trying to keep it a secret. Honestly, I really wasn't."


translate English day5_rs_T_93d3b582:


    pl "It must be so boring to be holed up in that room, unable to talk to anyone..."


translate English day5_rs_T_7ed51915:


    ev "Haaah..."


translate English day5_rs_T_84449c8c:


    nar "I'm sure she's frustrated by this staying a secret, too."


translate English day5_rs_T_187de9b5:


    ev "Oh, how did you like the incense I gave you?"


translate English day5_rs_T_ab99fdf4:


    pl "Oh. Um... I still have it.{w} It's really, really good, but given the situation being what it's been, I haven't had much chance to use it."


translate English day5_rs_T_a09f4c81:


    pl "I know it was a gift so sorry about that."


translate English day5_rs_T_02605af7:


    ev "Sometimes a gift still feels precious, even if all you do is hold onto it."


translate English day5_rs_T_ac1f4d87:


    ev "But if you're worried about it sitting around forever, why not give it to someone else?"


translate English day5_rs_T_d894fd66:


    pl "Am I allowed to do that?"


translate English day5_rs_T_7f76e1e5:


    ev "Why, certainly! Hearts are ever-changing.{w} The aroma I use was itself a gift from another."


translate English day5_rs_T_79bc621c:


    pl "...Why are you always burning incense, anyway?"


translate English day5_rs_T_927134a4:


    ev "Well, you see, the scent draws the little lambs here for me to gobble them up."


translate English day5_rs_T_163750ac:


    pl "R-Really...?"


translate English day5_rs_T_fad83f07:


    ev "Hee hee hee. No, of course not."


translate English day5_rs_T_660ba85e:


    pl "It doesn't sound like a joke when you say it...{w} Sometimes, I feel like the library itself is alive somehow."


translate English day5_rs_T_69bdde26:


    ev "Oh? Well, of course it's alive.{w} Where human hearts reside, so too does life."


translate English day5_rs_T_96647b1c:


    ev "This space has been alive for a millennium or more."


translate English day5_rs_T_1d9a71ae:


    ev "How many people have been inside its walls during all that time?"


translate English day5_rs_T_7f51a2e1:


    ev "We love this place very much.{w} What about you?"


translate English day5_rs_T_34235cf7:


    pl "I don't think I'd ever be that into a library, but I kinda like coming here."


translate English day5_rs_T_f0299dce:


    ev "Delightful! That alone is enough."


translate English day5_rs_T_561484c3:


    ev "But it seems like I've held you here overlong.{w} Please spend your time as you wish, so that you have no regrets."


translate English day5_rs_T_44c935e9:


    pl "Yep, sure thing. Thanks."


translate English day5_rs_T_e6492d90:


    nar "I stand there, watching her walk away through the library with slow steps."


translate English day5_rs_T_8baeb73f:


    nar "Once she's gone and I'm alone, I realize it feels like the fact that she was just here feels more like a dream to me."


translate English day5_rs_T_26459842:


    nar "Confused, I walk into the room, where I find Rose silently reading."


translate English day5_rs_T_9cf52166:


    nar "Seeing her sets my mind oddly at ease.{w} She stares up at me as I close the door and approach."


translate English day5_rs_T_242a910b:


    nar "Then, surprisingly, she doesn't say a word--she just buries her face in my clothes.{w} I hear sniffing noises."


translate English day5_rs_T_db36d35c:


